title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour into pie shells and bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: zucchini a la jennie
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in pan over low heat.
Cover bottom of pan with olive oil.
Simmer until half cooked.
Add tomatoes (skins removed), basil, garlic and garlic salt.
Cut potatoes in small chunks (simmer with zucchini and onions).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until tender, 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: fruit ham and pasta salad
directions: Chill unopened cans of oranges, pineapple and ham in the freezer for 10 minutes.

title: kentucky cobbler
directions: Put fruit in bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan. Combine ingredients.
Dot fruit with butter and spread crust mixture over fruit.
Pour 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup cold water over mixture.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Saute 2 cups chopped mushrooms and 1 cup saltine crackers (crushed).
Remove from pan and press into 9-inch pie plate to form crust.
Saute 1 cup scallions and place on crust.
Grate 1 1/2 cups Swiss cheese and place on top of scallions.
Blend together 3 eggs, 1 cup cottage cheese, basil, thyme and cayenne pepper.
Pour mixture into pie plate and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; wait 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: taco dip
directions: In small bowl, blend cream cheese, sour cream, avocado dip, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce.
Spread mixture in large serving plate.
Top with olives, chilies, onions, lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: fruit salad prize dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard and other ingredients (not celery seed) in blender.
Add celery seed and stir well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir all ingredients until blended in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with 1/2 cup butter.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes; stir until smoothy.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan lined with waxed paper.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: nell's jello relish
directions: Dissolve the first 4 ingredients.
Let cool off a bit, then add a little salt and pepper.
Refrigerate until set.
Stir a few times to distribute vegetables evenly.
If you prefer a bit more vegetables and horseradish, you may add to your own taste.
Really good with most meats, especially ham and corned beef.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Saute onion until wilted.
Add garlic.
Cut squash into 1-inch cubes.
Put into soup pot.
Add chicken broth, water and nutmeg; boil until squash is tender.
Remove from heat.
Add curry and pepper; stir.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and peanut butter. Whirl mix in blender or food processor, adding cream or evaporated milk.
Reheat.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Layer with raspberries, blueberries and strawberries.
Make the night before.

title: corn casserole
directions: Butter pan.
Mix corn and eggs.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in pan. Sprinkle crackers and 1/2 of the cheese on top.
Pour remaining corn on top.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Top with remaining cheese last 15 minutes.

title: plantation chicken
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add flour.
Stir and add milk, soup, pimento and chicken.
Bring to simmer and put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all together in 1 bowl; pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: kahlua sweetheart cake
directions: In small heatproof bowl blend cocoa, coffee and water.
Stir in 1/2 cup Kahlua; cool.
In large bowl beat butter, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add flour. Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with cocoa mixture, beating well after each addition.
Line bottom of two 9-inch round pans with parchment paper; lightly grease sides of pans.
Divide batter evenly between prepared pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven, 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Let cool in pans on wire racks 5 minutes.
Loosen edges; remove from pans.
Peel off parchment paper; cool completely on wire racks.
Brush bottom of each layer with 1 tablespoon of remaining Kahlua.
Prepare Kahlua Fudge Frosting.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together and pour over first ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and pepper.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: arlene's chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken. Let it cool. Chop it up. Put in large bowl; add all ingredients and mix well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, using only 1/2 package stuffing mix.
Place in buttered casserole and cover with remaining 1/2 package stuffing browned in butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
(Crackers may be substituted for stuffing for top.
I like half and half.)

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. In a double boiler, melt chocolate. Fold into cream cheese mixture with pecans. Spread into a greased 8-inch baking pan. Chill until ready to serve. Cut into squares. Yield: about 48 pieces.

title: orange-apricot dessert
directions: Drain oranges; combine with apricot yogurt.
Place in glass bowl and garnish with whipped topping and nuts.
Serve immediately.

title: farmer's fruit cake
directions: In large bowl, combine shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, flour, cloves, nutmeg and ginger and add alternately with sour milk.
Beat well. Fold in prunes and nuts and blend well.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir into dressing.
Divide and place half onto bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine squash, onions, soup, chestnuts and pimientos and pour over dressing.
Cover squash with remaining dressing and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple "flop" cake
directions: Stir first five ingredients with wooden spoon, not mixer. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: bar-b-q
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for 30 minutes stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Rinse and sort peas in a large pot.
Cover with water and soak for 4 hours.
Cook ham hocks for 2 hours.
Drain peas; add ham hock, onion, bell pepper, celery, red pepper and black pepper to peas.
Add water to cover.
Cook until peas are tender.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and celery in butter.
Stir in tuna, soup, mayonnaise, milk, mushrooms and pimento.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions and drain in colander.

title: beet jelly
directions: Bring the first 3 items to a rolling boil, then add the mixture of sugar and jello to it.
Return to boil and boil hard for 6 minutes.
Skim and pour into small jelly jars.
The beet juice you get from your beets after you've washed them and put water on them to cook, which you would normally throw away.
Really good.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar with vanilla and add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder 3 times and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Space about 1/4 inch apart. Flatten with spoon for crispness.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and put in airtight container.

title: pizza bagels
directions: Split bagels and place on cookie sheet.
Cover hole of bagel with a slice of pepperoni.
Add sauce and top with cheeses and additional pepperoni.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, cheese, egg substitute and pimiento in large bowl.
Mix well.
Combine 1 cup milk and flour in small bowl.
Stir smooth.
Add remaining 1 cup milk, sugar and next 3 ingredients. Stir well!
Add flour to corn.
Mix. Pour corn into 2-quart casserole coated with vegetable oil spray.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add hot water to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle peppers over corn.
Bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: beef 'n dumpling bake
directions: Place steak in 3-quart casserole. Cover with onion slices. Add bay leaf. Combine soups, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and flour. Pour over meat and onions. Cover. Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove from oven. Set oven at 400°. Remove bay leaf. Place peas on top of casserole and pepper rings in center. Drop dumplings by rounded teaspoons around pepper rings. Cover. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: angi's best cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Let rise one hour.
Roll 1/2 inch thin.
Spread with butter, brown sugar, and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut 1 inch thick. (Easiest way is to wrap a piece of dental floss around the roll, and pull on the ends of the floss.)
Place in a buttered pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake 350° for 15 minutes.
This makes a lot.
One half recipe fits into a 9x12 pan and a pie plate.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water for 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside. In a large, heavy pot, saut bacon, onions and celery over medium-high heat until celery is tender.
Drain bacon grease and return bacon, onions and celery to pot.
Add milk, water, chicken base, salt and pepper.
Heat over medium-high heat until very hot. Do not boil.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and onions.
Slice potatoes and lay in bottom of oven-safe casserole dish or Pyrex. Smear 1 can cream of celery soup over the potatoes (not diluted).
Lay browned pork chops and onions on top.
Smear 1 can cream of mushroom soup (not diluted) on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Cut a loaf of stale bread into 1/4-inch cubes. Season with melted butter, thyme, basil, oregano, salt and pepper. Bake until crisp. In a large bowl, grind anchovies to a paste-like consistency. Stir in all remaining ingredients except romaine lettuce. Tear romaine lettuce into large pieces and place in a large bowl. Pour salad dressing over lettuce and toss salad. Serve immediately.

title: crunchy topped pumpkin cake
directions: Whisk eggs in a 2-quart microwave-proof bowl or casserole. Blend in next 5 ingredients.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 4 minutes or until hot and thickened, stirring once halfway through. Pour into microwave-proof, 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Melt margarine in microwave.
Drizzle evenly over cake mix.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 8 minutes or until top is set, rotating dish twice.
Place dish under conventional oven broiler for 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Refrigerate.
Cut in squares.
Serves 12, 213 calories per serving, 10.3 grams fat and 1 mg. cholesterol.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain excess oil.
Cook macaroni and cheese; mix together with hamburger.
Layer with hamburger, Pizza Quick and macaroni and cheese, ending with Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: baked seafood casserole(joshua thomas chapel cookbook)
directions: Combine crabmeat, shrimp, mayonnaise, green pepper, onion, celery, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: maple-walnut chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Put in a large bowl; cool slightly.
Combine flour and soda.
Stir sugar and eggs into chocolate mixture until well combined.
Stir in flour mixture, milk and extract until blended. Stir in walnuts.

title: homemade freezer slaw
directions: Cover cabbage, peppers, carrot and salt with water.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse well.
Boil vinegar, sugar and water together.
Cool, then pour over slaw.
Put in container and freeze.

title: mini blinis
directions: Blend the egg yolk, 1/4 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Roll bread slices flat.
Spread mixture and roll up.
Cut in half.
Dip in the melted butter.
Roll in mixture of 1 1/2 cups sugar and cinnamon. Freeze.
Bake seam side down at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hash brown bake
directions: In a bowl, mix hash browns, sour cream, soup and cheese. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix corn flakes, butter and garlic salt together.
Spread on top of hash brown mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese.
Spread 1/2 in each pie shell. Cover with sliced bananas.
Sprinkle with a little lemon juice. Cover with 1/2 can of pie filling per pie.
Chill overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put cooked and cut up chicken in bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix the soups with 2 cups of chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Mix herb stuffing with 1 cup of broth and pour on top of soups.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: green tomato chow chow relish
directions: Bring to a boil and boil gently for 30 minutes or longer if too juicy.
Remove and add 2 tablespoons turmeric.
Pack in hot jar.
This makes 10 or 12 pints.

title: yellow squash relish
directions: Wash, peel and chop squash.
Add onion, peppers and pimientos. Sprinkle with salt.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Rinse (real good) and drain.
Bring sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and turmeric to boil.
Add squash mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer until heated through.
Pour into clean hot jars, 1/2-inch headroom.
Seal.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Put into buttered baking dish.
Bake until firm at 300°.

title: quick cheese danish
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice together; set aside.
Unfold 1 package of crescent roll dough into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, pinching together to form one sheet of dough. Then, spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Unfold second package of crescent rolls on top, pinching together to form one sheet of dough.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring just until all dry ingredients are moist.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Yields 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Combine margarine, water, peanut butter and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well until blended and pour onto a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
(It will be a very thin batter.)
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(If using a 9 x 13 greased and floured pan, bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.)
Cool and frost.

title: spicy dry black-eyed peas
directions: Cook dry peas according to package directions until 2/3 done. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until peas are tender.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower
by
package
directions. Drain. Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put in
a
1/2 quart casserole dish.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: wafer cake
directions: Grind vanilla wafers.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add 6 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla wafer crumbs.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 350° until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Add biscuits and shake until coated.
Place coated biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
Layer nuts with biscuits.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with more nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cook 30 minutes, then invert on a plate.

title: pineapple delight congealed salad
directions: Dissolve both pkgs. of gelatin in water.
Add remaining ingredients, and stir thoroughly.
Pour into mold, and chill in refrigerator until firm.
The horseradish is very important, but does not predominate the taste.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: roquefort cheese ball
directions: In a small mixing bowl at low speed, beat cheeses for 2 minutes.
Add green onions, optional wine or vermouth and mustard. Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes or until fluffy.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
With wet hands, shape into a 3-inch ball and roll in nuts.
Decorate with parsley and serve with crackers.

title: apple cake
directions: Sprinkle the fruit with lemon juice aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, adding flour last.
Fold in fruit just before baking. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon sheet pie
directions: Mix like pie crust. Pat down dough on cookie sheet with a little lip. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: spinach cheese puffs(12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry. Stir with a fork until well blended; set aside. Cut pastry into twenty-five 2 x 2-inch squares. Place spinach mixture onto the center of each square. Transfer squares to an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes (or longer until pastry is golden brown). Remove from oven and serve.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over melted butter or margarine.
Drain peaches (reserve juice) and arrange with cherries over the sugar mixture.
Mix cake as directed on box, using reserved peach juice for all or part of liquid.
Pour mixed cake batter over sugar, butter and fruit; mix. Bake at 350° until done (45 to 50 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes, turn upside down onto large platter.
Good warm with whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken and save broth.
Melt butter in a Dutch oven or large stew pot.
Add onions, celery and carrot.
Cook until onions are golden.
Add broth, rice and seasonings.
Cover and cook on low heat until rice is done, about 20 minutes.
Add chopped chicken and simmer about 15 minutes more.
Delicious!

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a well-greased cast-iron frypan.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Place
cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean layer pans. Prick each
cake	with
serving
fork
at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve Jell-O
in	boiling
water.
Add cold water and pour carefully over cakes.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: hot sausage in sour cream
directions: Fry the sausage until well done (cut brown and serve sausages in half). Pour off grease. Place in chafing dish. Pour chutney, wine and sour cream in skillet. Simmer a few minutes and pour over sausage. Serve hot. Serves 12.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil, then add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Then add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, floured nuts and diced apples.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine ingredients and press
into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter and sugar slowly until stiff enough to roll in balls.
Form into balls on wax paper.
Chill 1 hour.

title: white grape salad
directions: Wash grapes and cut in half. Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Mix about 1 oz. pineapple juice with cream cheese until you have the consistency of thick soup. Add all ingredients; coat well with cream cheese mixture. Chill and serve.

title: hot wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients; sweeten to taste.
Heat and serve.
Can be refrigerated and reheated.

title: "plaki" - fish-onions-raisins
directions: Combine chopped onions, tomato sauce and oil in pan.
Season with salt and pepper; cook about 20 minutes.
Mixture should be juicy.
Add raisins and parsley and mix.
Pour into baking dish.

title: grandma's polish bread(babka)
directions: Combine yeast and water; set aside.
Mix all ingredients, adding yeast mixture last.
Knead.
Cover and let stand 1 hour. Beat down mixture; let rise 1 more hour. Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan the pecans and coconut.
Mix German chocolate cake as box directs.
Pour over coconut and pecans in pan, then mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, margarine and vanilla.
Spoon over cake mixture.
Do not try to smooth out.
Leave as dropped from spoon and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: quiche
directions: For best results, heat pie crust in a 400° oven for about 5 minutes.
Saute onion in oleo in saucepan for about 5 minutes. Pour in pie crust.
Add grated cheese, then eggs.
Season eggs with dash of salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with bacon, ham, sausage or Spam.
Good wintertime evening meal.

title: egg coffee
directions: Heat 6 cups water to boiling.
Beat egg and 2 tablespoons water together.
Stir 2 tablespoons egg mixture into 3/4 cup ground coffee.
Add enough cold water to completely moisten grounds; pour into boiling water.
Heat to rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add dash of cold water.
Makes 6 to 8 cups.

title: salmon roll
directions: Mash salmon with fork.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Shape into roll (log) with hands.
Roll into cream cheese, then pecans and chill.

title: curt's 14 day pickles
directions: Cut up thick slices of cucumbers, enough to fill a gallon glass jar.
Add 1 cup salt and 1 gallon of water and let soak for 7 days.
Drain 7th day.
Wash well and drain.
Next, soak 1 tablespoon alum and 1 gallon warm water overnight.
Next morning, drain and let soak in clear cold water for 2 hours.
Drain.
Heat 1 quart vinegar, 2 quarts sugar, 1 tablespoon pickling spice and 1 tablespoon turmeric.
Let come to a boil, pour over pickles.
Do this each day for 7 days.
Seal in jars on 7th day.
Jars should be hot.

title: sam lee's famous clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon crisp and keep to the side.
Use bacon oil to cook carrots, onion and celery.
Set aside.
Cook potatoes.
Set aside.
Melt 1 cube butter.
Add flour and brown.
Add clam juice slowly.
Add half and half plus whipped cream.
Add clams including juice from can.
Add corn, carrots, celery, potatoes and onion. Bring to a boil and thicken.
Use cornstarch base.
Add bacon and butter.
Simmer. Do not let burn. Enjoy!
(Do not overcook potatoes.)

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening and butter.
Mix until crumbly. Add water.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add to butter mixture 1/2 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spread dough into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Yield: 3 dozen cookies.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein .5 g, fat 5 g, calories 75.
One cookie = 1/2 bread exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: hummus dip
directions: Blend all together in blender until dip consistency.
Serve with pita bread or crackers.
Garnish with mint.

title: seafood gumbogroves, texas
directions: Make roux in thick cast iron pot, by stirring flour and oil on very low heat until dark brown.
Transfer to big gumbo pot.
Add water, tomatoes, cook about 45 minutes and add celery, bell pepper, okra, onion and garlic.
Add shrimp, oysters and crab meat, season to taste with salt, pepper and tabasco.
Cook slowly for 1 hour. If too thick, add more water.
Serve in bowl over hot rice.

title: tortellini and vegetables
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Parcook vegetables and drain.
Melt butter in a pan.
Add tortellini and vegetables.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and sprinkle bread crumbs over mixture, just enough to hold together. Makes a great side dish.

title: turkey or chicken surprise
directions: Mix stuffing according to directions.
Mix together sour cream and pineapple.
In 9 x 13-inch pan put 1/2 the stuffing in bottom of pan.
Add diced meat, pour over pineapple mixture, then crumble on the rest of the stuffing.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add mushroom soup, cream cheese, salt, pepper and paprika.
Stir until well blended, then cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Blend and freeze first 6 ingredients solid.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before using.
Chop up and pour 7-Up over.
Serve. Yield:
2 punch bowls full.

title: pumpkin blossom cookies
directions: Beat milk and pumpkin until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop 1 1/2 inches apart on baking sheet. Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned at 375°.
Press candy in cookie immediately after baking or about 1 minute before done.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar and salt and beat well.
Add eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and beat well.
Put in a 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan (well-greased).
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Remove from pan and pour over hot bread 1/2 cup sugar and juice of one lemon.
Freezes well.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in electric skillet. Brown chicken on both sides. Add soup and water, mixing until blended. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add rice and cook until rice is tender. It's ready to eat.

title: special pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: snowbound casserole
directions: In a large skillet (or electric frying pan), saute onion and celery until soft.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, curry powder, pepper and green pepper.
Add dashes of hot sauce to taste (optional).

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook pie crust.
Combine 1 1/3 cups sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium-size saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil and is thick.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks slightly in small bowl.
Slowly blend in 1/2 cup of hot mixture. Slowly stir back into rest of hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly over low heat 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Cover with wrap and refrigerate until cold (3 hours). Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy white.
Sprinkle in 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stands in peaks.
Spread on pie. Cook at 425° for 3 to 5 minutes until brown.

title: maurine moon's mexican rice
directions: Cook rice about half done.
Chop 1/2 cup bacon or ham.
Add to heavy skillet and cook slowly.
Add 2 chopped onions and chopped bell pepper; simmer with bacon.
Do not scorch.
Add chili powder to taste.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Add half cooked rice, chili powder and salt to taste.
Cook slowly, stirring to keep from sticking.
Garnish with parsley.

title: grapefruit chiffon cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the middle.
Add in order egg yolks, oil, peel and juice. Beat briefly until smooth.

title: japanese pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Heat chicken pieces, water, salt, garlic and bay leaf to boiling in Dutch oven; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth; strain broth.
Refrigerate chicken and broth.
When cool, remove chicken from bones (skin can be removed, if desired).
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Skim excess fat from broth and place broth and chicken in Dutch oven.
Stir in celery, onion, tomatoes (with liquid), frozen okra, corn (with liquid), rice and pepper sauce. Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until okra and rice are tender, 20 to 30 minutes. Garnish with snipped parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gulf coast canned mullet
directions: Make a brine of water and salt.
Soak fillets 1 hour; drain. Pack mullet to lower neckband of quart jars.
Add no water, but pack fish firmly in jar.
Add Zatarain's Creole seasoning to each quart.
Process 100 minutes at 10 pound pressure.

title: coffee cake
directions: Crumble over pie filling and nuts.
Top with sugar coated flakes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not overmix or overbake.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box.
Using a large mixing bowl, mix yellow cake mix, cooked pudding and 1/2 cup oil.
After ingredients are thoroughly mixed, pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread the butterscotch tidbits and nuts on top of the uncooked cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes in
350° preheated oven.
Very delicious.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into small cookies.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tropical cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip and drained pineapple.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: apple tray
directions: Soften cream cheese and add other ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Serve at room temperature.
Garnish with a cinnamon stick.
Slice green and red apples of equal size and shape into eighths.
Core each slice.
Dip in pineapple juice and part water (or other citrus juice) to prevent discoloring of apples.
Piece apples back together as halves, alternating green and red.
Place "striped" apple halves onto tray of lettuce leaves, circling apple dip.
May add grapes and/or pears to the tray.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Soak mushrooms for 3 to 4 hours and bring to a boil in a small amount of water.
Add the broth and simmer, covered, for half an hour.
Melt the butter; blend in the flour, salt and pepper.
Add the stock gradually while stirring.
Stir in sour cream just before serving.
Reheat, but don't let the soup boil.
Add more seasoning to taste.

title: summer delite
directions: Place lawn chair or hammock in or out of direct sunlight, your choice.
Open beer and drink along with your choice of chips, pretzels or popcorn.

title: pear-pecan salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and reserve 1 cup of liquid.
Bring juice to a boil on high heat.
Remove from heat and add lemon-flavored gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Place pears and cream cheese in blender container and blend until creamy consistency.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Add pecans.
If using whipping cream, whip and fold in gelatin mixture.
If using Cool Whip, fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss with french dressing 1 1/2 pounds ground beef browned with 1/2 chopped onion.
Add 1 package of taco seasoning - cook till done and drain.
You can put salsa or taco sauce on it if desired. Mix all together just before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Add mixed dry ingredients and chocolate cut in small pieces.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Stir a small amount of mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks and return mixture to double boiler.
Stir until coagulates (2 or 3 minutes) and remove from fire.
Add butter and vanilla; beat thoroughly with rotary beater or electric mixer.
Cool.
Place in a baked shell.
Cover with meringue made with egg whites.
Bake in 300° oven for about 20 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Pour pie filling into prepared dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir to form soft dough.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into pie filling to form dumplings.
Cover with lid or foil and bake 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake additional 15 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crock-pot turkey breast
directions: Place all in crock-pot on low.
Cook 8 hours.
You might have to thicken soup for gravy.

title: marinade for lamb
directions: Make slits in lamb; rub in marinade.

title: 4 layer cake
directions: Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Set aside to cool.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food grinder or food processor; stir in sugar to blend.
Set aside.
Dissolve gelatin dessert in water; cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Add to cranberry mixture. Add oranges, nuts and pineapple.
Stir well; pour into lightly oiled 8-cup mold.
Chill overnight.
Unmold.

title: grandma's lazy daisy cake topping
directions: Heat oleo and sugar until melted.
Add milk and blend well. Add nuts and mix well.
Spread over cool cake.
Slide under broiler about 3 minutes, until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients well.
Form into loaf.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Pour catsup over loaf and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: spinach and artichoke party dip
directions: Combine light sour cream and party dip mix in medium bowl. Stir in artichoke, spinach and pimientos.
Cut slice off top of round loaf of bread.
Hollow out center of bread leaving 1-inch shell.
Reserve bread pieces for dipping.
Spoon dip into bread shell.
Serve warm or cold.
To serve warm, bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cover loaf with foil if browning too quickly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until brown.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix meat mixture with the pizza sauce, oregano and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour in roaster pan; sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts (about 30 minutes).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Add all of ingredients to egg mixture and stir.
Pour into greased 10-inch square pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: clam and corn chowder
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan bring chicken broth to a boil. Meanwhile, heat oil in a skillet and cook onion, garlic and celery for 10 minutes or until slightly soft.
Stir in dill and thyme. Add cooked vegetables to broth along with potatoes.
Cover pot and simmer about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in creamed corn and simmer 5 minutes, then add milk and undrained clams.
Simmer until heated through (do not boil) about 5 minutes. Adjust salt if necessary.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons chopped parsley if you like.
Makes about 10 cups (135 calories each, if made with low-fat milk).

title: skinny meat loaf
directions: Place bread and onion in food processor and whirl.
Add tomatoes, marjoram, paprika, parsley and pepper; whirl.
Combine beef, turkey, egg substitute and bread mixture in bowl.
Pack into six cup ring mold.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Unmold onto platter.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening, and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten until lemon colored.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavoring.
Spoon in 10-inch bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for about 10 minutes.
Put icing over cake.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Lightly grease baking dish.
Place bread on bottom of dish. Spread sausage on bread and sprinkle cheese on sausage.
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: english apple pie
directions: Fill round pie dish with a layer of chopped apples. Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together, add salt to taste.
Pour into shallow baking dish, dot with butter, sprinkle with pepper.
Bake in 350° oven until inserted knife comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: lemon butter
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar; mix well. Add rest of ingredients. Cook in a double boiler until thick. Serve on toast, muffins or Maryland biscuits.

title: heroes
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Layer lettuce, tomato, onions and sprinkle with dressing.
Top with meats and cheeses and sprinkle with a small dash of dressing.
Any other cold cut or cheese of your desire may be used instead.
Put top on and cut diagonally.

title: polish cabbage
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp. Remove bacon into a stewing pot. Saute the cabbage in the bacon grease and add to stew pot.
Add the tomatoes to this and boil to finish cooking the cabbage. Thicken the mixture with flour that has been dissolved in water. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: crab salad(a light, elegant luncheon salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.
Tastes great the next day, too.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: tomato rice soup
directions: Saute onions in small frying pan.
Dice and boil potatoes. Leave potatoes in water.
Add rice and alphabets, then tomato soup.
Ready to serve when potatoes and pasta are done.

title: stuffed yellow squash
directions: Simmer whole squash 8 to 10 minutes until tender, but firm. Slice in half; scoop out center, leaving firm shell.
Combine pulp and remaining ingredients except butter.
Fill squash shells and place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Dot with butter. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Mix in soup until hot.
Add chopped onion and put in casserole dish.
Put Tater Tots on top. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top for approximately 5 minutes or until completely melted.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: mexicale casserole
directions: Prepare cornmeal mix to package directions.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Brown ground beef in large skillet and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, chopped tomatoes and corn.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour in baking dish, then pour prepared cornmeal mix over beef mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Put milk in saucepan.
Add cheese pieces and butter.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Do not boil.
Put macaroni into baking dish (add sliced hot dogs).
Add cheese liquid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line cookie sheet with crescent roll dough spread out like pizza. Bake until golden brown (375° for approximately 10 minutes). Mix dressing mix, mayo and cream cheese. Spread on cooled crust. Sprinkle desired shredded vegetables and cheese on cream cheese mixture. Press them down into mixture. Refrigerate until set or overnight.

title: peanut butter cookie pop
directions: You will also need 10 popsicle sticks.

title: campfire corn on the cob
directions: Soak ears of corn still in husk for at least one hour in water.
While the corn is soaking, build fire over loosened dirt, let coals burn down.
Pull husk back and remove silk; put salt, pepper, and butter on corn.
Pull husk back onto corn.
Wrap in foil.
Pull coals aside and dig into loosened dirt to make hole 6 to 8 inches deep. Place corn in hole pull coals back over buried corn.
Build another small fire to keep coals hot.
Roast 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbeque sauce for spareribs(yield: serving for 4 people.)
directions: 1. Before starting the sauce, place the ribs in a pot with water and pour in one beer.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for one hour.
This will make the meat tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Drop small amounts on ungreased cookie sheet to bake.

title: freezer punch
directions: Mix all according to package directions.
Put in freezer, being sure to stir every hour.
Keep in freezer until slushy. When ready to serve, add 1 bottle of chilled 7-Up.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
With a pastry blender, cut in butter until very fine. Pare, core and thinly slice apples.
Arrange in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with flour mixture.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven until apples are tender and topping is browned, 30 minutes.
Serve hot, topped with vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: *May use 1 to 2 blocks firm tofu and omit eggs and cottage cheese.

title: pear preserves
directions: Slice pears, pour sugar over and soak overnight.
Cook until bubbly and thick. Add a slice of lemon if desired.

title: pollo borracho
directions: Pour 2 tablespoons oil into Dutch oven or large casserole. Over low heat, add onion rings, parsley, sesame seed, whole black peppers, cinnamon, cloves and bay leaf.
Mix. Add chicken.
Pour over chicken remaining oil, vinegar and sherry.
Add olives, chiles and salt to taste.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, turning a few times. May be baked at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with steamed white rice. Serves 6.

title: excellent divinity
directions: Using a heavy saucepan, dissolve sugars, water and syrup over medium heat. Boil until candy thermometer reaches 236°. Pour one half of syrup slowly, beating all the while, over the stiffly beaten egg whites. Cook remainder of syrup to 252°, then beat into whites. Add nuts and vanilla extract and continue beating until gloss of candy lessens and will stand up in peaks. When firm, drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper. Mixture sets up quickly. This is really delicious and makes lots of candy.

title: sausage
directions: Bring 3 cups water to a boil.
Blend remaining ingredients, except oats, until smooth.
Add to the 3 cups of boiling water, then add oats.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Shape into patties or links.
Bake on a nonstick cookie sheet at 350°.
Cook patties 30 minutes on one side, 20 minutes on the other.
Links or meatballs, cook for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and grated zucchini to the eggs.
(If zucchini is too large, remove the seeds before grating.)
Mix lightly, but not well.
Add dry ingredients.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cook onion and bacon together.
Add with drippings to cooked, diced potatoes.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten, then Worcestershire and celery seed.
Add olives and cheese.
Add dash of sugar, salt and pepper.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Saute
onion
and green pepper in melted butter.
Brown ground beef
with	onion and green pepper; let pan juices cook down
or drain.
Add
Worcestershire
sauce	and cook about 2 minutes longer.

title: russian mints
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flavoring and chocolate.
Spoon half of wafers into bottom of cupcake liners.
Spoon the chocolate mixture on top and cover with the rest of wafer crumbs.
Top with dab of whipped cream and cherry.
Place in freezer.
Makes about 20.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream 3/4 cup of sugar and margarine.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In a small bowl, stir together the flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Stir this mixture into margarine mixture.
In a small bowl, mix the 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls and roll in the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cereal cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream brown sugar, sugar and butter.
Blend flour, baking powder, soda, salt, eggs and vanilla into creamed mixture.
Stir in cereal, rolled oats, coconut and peanuts.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray large pizza pan or large cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
Pat out sugar cookie roll to desired thickness.
Bake per package directions.
Let cool.

title: life saver frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick and cool (do this while cake is baking).
Cream sugar, shortening and butter well and add to cooled flour mixture; add vanilla and salt.
Beat until fluffy and about the consistency of whipped cream.
This is a life saver when you need icing but are out of confectioners sugar.

title: cheesy oven fries
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut each into 8 wedges.
Combine cheese and the next 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Dip potato wedge in melted margarine.
Arrange in single layer in lightly buttered pan. Sprinkle cheese mixture over.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 40 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and browned.

title: vern's ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and fill 4 quart freezer to fill line.

title: clothes line candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball in water.
Add dates and boil 3 minutes.
Take off stove and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until almost hard.
Pour into a wet cloth. Hang on clothes line to get cold and hard.
Cut into slices.

title: cornbread or cornpone
directions: Combine egg, sugar, salt and butter.
Add milk; mix well.
Add all dry ingredients.
May be a little stiff.
Bake at 375° (usually takes 25 or 30 minutes).

title: rice krispies peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the margarine, powdered sugar, peanut butter and cereal together.
Form into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips, chocolate bar and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate with toothpicks.
Cool on wax paper.

title: oriental skillet supper
directions: In heavy skillet, quickly cook green pepper and celery in oil until crisp-tender.
Remove; set aside.
Add meat to skillet; cook.
Combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add to skillet.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add celery, pepper and tomato.
Heat through.
Toss rice with ginger.
Serve over ginger rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: milk punch
directions: Mix
together
milk,
orange
juice
and sugar.
Return liquid to
the cartons or pour into ice cube trays and freeze until solid.
When you are ready to make punch, use 1/2 gallon block
at a time.
Place frozen mixture into punch bowl, break into
smaller chunks and pour 2 liters of ginger ale over the frozen chunks. Makes a large punch bowl full.

title: saltine toffee cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line cookie sheet with crackers in a single layer. In a saucepan, combine sugar and butter; boil for 3 minutes. Immediately pour over saltines and spread to cover crackers completely. Bake 5 to 6 minutes.

title: seven up cake
directions: You will need a tubular baking pan.

title: mom's cheese ball
directions: Mix together well cheeses and bacon bits.
Chill on waxed paper in bowl.
When firm, roll in nuts; place cherry in middle and chill until served.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar in large mixing bowl; set aside.
Mix beaten egg with orange juice, rind, margarine and hot water.
Fold flour mixture until blended.
Do not beat.
Gently fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or smaller pans of choice.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes; test in center with wooden pick.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: evelyn wagner's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly with a fork.
Mix sugar and flour together. Add to beaten eggs.
Stir in syrup, vanilla, salt and butter. Cover unbaked shell with pecans.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; turn heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes more.
Filling will be slightly less set in the center than the edges.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip if desired.

title: smokies or wieners
directions: Simmer ketchup and grape jelly until melted. Add wieners or Smokies and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Serve warm.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Blend dry ingredients in a separate bowl. Mix into shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Spread in well-greased pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and 1 stick oleo.
Spread over mixture.
Let cool and cut.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Grease 9-inch tube pan or 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream shortening, sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add beaten egg.
Mix and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture.
Roll in ball between palms of hands. Press with fork.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Combine in a jar and shake until well blended.
Pour over steak and marinate several hours, turning once or twice.
Broil, basting 2 or 3 times.
Can also be used as roast (London broil) and on the grill.

title: english green beans
directions: Cook green beans with seasonings for approximately 2 hours, until very tender.
Cook them down so there isn't a lot of water left in them.
Add onion and tomatoes and cook for another hour or so.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: picadillo
directions: Place venison beef or pork in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.
Cook until meat is brown.
Drain any excess fat.
Stir in flour, tomato paste, salt, pepper, garlic and ground cumin to coat meat evenly.
Add water and vegetables.
Bring liquid to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over dirty rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately top cookie with candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Cool completely.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Note:
Can add more sour cream, if thinner dip is desired.

title: honey hot fudge topping
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Stir in cocoa and cornstarch.
Add honey, water and a shake of salt.
Boil until it is thick; remove from heat.
Stir in mini marshmallows.
Serve over ice cream or pound cake.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: mint chip ice cream
directions: In a saucepan, combine eggs, milk, sugar and salt. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture reaches 160° and coats a metal spoon. Cool to room temperature. Stir in cream, vanilla, peppermint extract and food coloring. Refrigerate for 2 hours. Stir in chocolate chips. Fill ice cream freezer cylinder 2/3 full; freeze according to manufacturer's directions. Refrigerate remaining mixture until ready to freeze. Yield: 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cajun meat loaf
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add first 6 ingredients.
Stir about 5 or 6 minutes.
Add catsup and milk.
Mix well and cool.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Rinse kidney beans, drain and combine all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling, water and sugar into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix well. Sprinkle 1 box Duncan Hines yellow cake mix (dry) over the cherry pie mixture.
Slice up margarine and place on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick fruit dish
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail. Add the pineapple (plus juice).
Add the pudding.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix gently.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter; set aside.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Prepare brownie mix by directions.
Spread 1/2 of mix evenly on a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Place remaining half on an additional 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° approximately 10 to 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
(Be careful not to burn.)
Allow to cool to room temperature.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash and slice okra.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Combine eggs and buttermilk.
Add okra.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine flour and meal.
Drain okra, small portions at a time, using slotted spoon.
Dredge okra, small portions at a time in flour mixture. Put 2 to 3 inches of oil in a Dutch oven or heavy saucepan.
Heat and fry okra to golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake according to box.
Mix nuts and coconut.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Pour cake mixture over this.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo. Pour over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and turn out.
This will look like it isn't done, but will set up after it cools.

title: dirty dessert
directions: Make pudding, then break up the cookies in a bowl. Spread part of the cookies on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, then one layer of pudding on top of the cookies, then 1 layer of Cool Whip. Continue making layers until all ingredients are used up. Refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl and blend well.
Pour into crusts and chill for several hours.

title: apple pumpkin pie
directions: Pour apple pie filling into unbaked pie shell.
Combine cornstarch, spices, salt and sugar.
Add pumpkin, molasses and melted butter.
Blend well.
Combine milk and eggs.
Stir in; pour over apple filling.
(To avoid spills, add last of milk and egg mixture with pie on oven rack--pan will be brimful).
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in pie comes out clean. Chill, then garnish with whipped cream.

title: you name it casserole
directions: Mix all spices with hamburger.
Layer hamburger, potatoes, corn and onions.
Add tomato soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°; grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In medium bowl, beat egg, melted shortening, orange juice and water.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir until ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts.
Pour into prepared loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Store in refrigerator overnight before slicing or freeze.
Makes one loaf.

title: pink lemonade ice milk cake
directions: Slice cake horizontally into 3 layers; set aside.
Combine softened ice milk, pink lemonade and chopped strawberries in a large bowl; stir well.
Place bottom layer of cake in an 8-inch tube pan.
Spread half of ice milk mixture over cake and top with middle layer of cake.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Spread remaining ice milk mixture over middle layer of cake and top with remaining cake layer.
Cover and freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Slice into wedges.
Yield:
16 servings (129 calories per serving).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Butter a casserole well.
Place sliced potatoes on bottom. Cover with the orange slices.
Add chops, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cook in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours, or until chops are done.

title: homemade hominy
directions: Cover with water and boil until the skin slips from the grain. Wash well in several waters after removing the skins.
Cook the grains until tender.

title: herbed tomato soup
directions: Heat margarine, in medium-size nonaluminum saucepan, over medium heat, until melted and bubbly.
Add 2 tablespoons marjoram and garlic; saute 1 minute or until garlic is tender, but not browned.
Add tomatoes.
Bring to a boil; cook 15 minutes or until mixture is reduced to 3 cups.

title: ground beef dish
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
In large skillet, combine ground beef, onion, celery and mushrooms and cook until beef is browned and celery is tender; drain.
In medium bowl, blend soup, milk, sour cream and cheese.
Combine noodles, ground beef mixture and soup mixture; mix well.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven just until hot, about 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves about 6.

title: berry barbecue chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 2-quart baking dish. Mix together sauce, dressing and soup mix. Spoon over chicken. Cover with wax paper. Cook in the microwave on High 20 to 25 minutes. Turn 1/4 turn after 10 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve chilled.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce, simmer at least 15 minutes.
Put spaghetti into glass baking dish, add beef and sauce and mix well, reserving enough sauce and beef to spread on top.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw and let rise 1 loaf of frozen bread dough (follow package directions).
On a slightly greased (oil) cookie sheet, spread dough into a rectangle.
Press pepperoni onto dough.
Spread Mozzarella cheese over pepperoni and then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Roll lengthwise and pinch all edges.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: egg custard(old fashioned)
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Combine with sugar to which the flour has been added.
Add milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and dot with slices of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add tomato sauce, kidney beans and vinegar.
Stir in spices; cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut macaroon cookies
directions: Combine coconut, sugar and flour, then add egg whites, almond extract, then last almonds.
Stir good.
Drop teaspoon size on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove stems from peppers and remove seeds and membrane, wash and drain.
Place in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: chicken breast with crab stuffing
directions: Sprinkle inside of chicken breast with salt and flatten by pounding.
Top with filling made of egg, stuffing, soup, crabmeat, green pepper, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Roll up chicken around stuffing.
Dip in melted butter and then cereal crumbs.
Place seam side down in an ungreased shallow baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sangria
directions: Put ice in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour wine, Coca-Cola, and Collins mix over ice.
Last, add sugar and stir.
Float fruit slices on Sangria for decoration.
If you want to add a kick to your Sangria, add 1 cup brandy.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Blend chicken soup and milk in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in cubed chicken, cooked rice, cheese and peas.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into large casserole and freeze.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients into meat with your hand. Spread into casserole dish. Top with
additional ketchup. Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook and drain zucchini.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. In skillet, melt butter, add sour cream, cheese, salt and paprika.
When cheese is melted, remove from heat and add egg yolk and chives.
Pour over zucchini.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top, then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined eggs, milk and margarine.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: quiche
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: delicious brownie icing
directions: Melt chocolate, Crisco, salt and vanilla in saucepan at low heat.
Add milk, confectioners sugar and pecans.
Add more milk if too thick.
Pour over cooled brownies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Mix soups together and pour over green beans.
Add drained water chestnuts.
Stir together.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into steak.
By pounding it helps tenderize it. Then fry the steak
real
fast
to
brown
on both sides. Turn heat down to medium,
slice
onion over the steak and add tomato sauce then let cook for
about an hour and a half.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: rev. rose deer roast
directions: Wash off roast in cold water; cut off excess fat.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, or rub with cloves of garlic.
Cut onion into slices.
Put onion and bacon over.
Wrap in foil.
Bake for 3 hours at 325°.

title: momma's tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Arrange tuna on top.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper.
Mix soup and milk; pour over casserole.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.
Serve with salad.

title: frankfurters buon gusto
directions: Cook bacon in heavy skillet until almost crisp.
Add onions and cook for 3 minutes.
Add frankfurters and peppers and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add olives, capers and seasonings.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over ingredients in skillet.
Cook until eggs are set, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken with onion and garlic.
Warm tortillas in oil; layer meat, olives and cheese in tortilla.
Roll up tortilla; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chili and enchilada sauce over top. Sprinkle with remaining cheeses.
If desired, sprinkle olives and parsley over top.
Another option is to spoon guacamole down center of pan over enchiladas and garnish with olives.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This dish can be made in advance and frozen until ready to cook.

title: mary inglis' crab cakes
directions: Check crab for any pieces of shell or cartilage.
Mix picked-over crabmeat, bread, mayonnaise, milk and mustard.
Form mixture into 6 crab cakes.
Fry or saute crab cakes in oil.
Makes 6 large crab cakes.

title: butter brickle bars
directions: Pour melted butter in oblong pan.
Add almond flavoring if desired.
Add remaining ingredients as listed previously.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan. Combine dry ingredients; stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix just until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix.
Put over chopped vegetables.
Let sit for about 24 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients; mix by hand thoroughly.
Make small balls; place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Makes 100 small Sausage Balls.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Fold mayonnaise and yogurt together.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line pie crust with peaches.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Cut in flour and egg.
Add vanilla and then spread over peaches.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: vegetable puff
directions: Combine melted butter, sour cream, Parmesan and eggs.
When thoroughly mixed, add Mozzarella and seasonings.
Defrost vegetables and drain; add to mixture, then add flour and stir. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Top will brown and middle will be firm.

title: italian omelet
directions: Fry potatoes in a little oil until tender.
Stir constantly. Add eggs, cheese and Italian salami, beaten together.
Do not stir. (Let form as a pie, about 5 minutes on low fire).
Turn and cook on other side about 5 minutes.
Turn onto plate as pie.
Enjoy.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk and bananas. Blend dry ingredients and stir into egg mix.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool before slicing.
(Cracks normal.)

title: chocolate peanut crispies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Gradually stir in cereal and peanuts.
Stir in chocolate morsels and press mixture into lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Let cool and cut.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased casserole. Sprinkle parsley flakes on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
butter for 10 minutes on high speed. Add one
egg at a time and beat after each egg.
Sift and add all dry ingredients and milk to eggs, then fold in coconut and flavoring. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients and blend. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cinnamon twists(serves 5 - 2 rolls per person)
directions: Use a pastry cloth and stockinet covered rolling pin when rolling pie crust.
You will use less flour, fewer strokes and have a tender, more flaky pie crust.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Easy to make and real good.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and salt; blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into mixture very carefully.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then lower to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: paradise peach surprise
directions: Combine flour, sugar and pecans.
Add margarine; mix well. Press this mixture in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread over the cooled crust.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water. Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Put peach slices over cheese mixture.
Spoon chilled gelatin over peaches.
Cover and chill until firm.
This may need adjusting; for some ovens, 25 minutes is too long.

title: custardy corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add 1 cup milk, egg and butter.
Pour into a baking pan and put 1/2 cup milk on top.
Do not stir.
This will be soft like spoon bread.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, oil and eggs together by hand or slowly with a mixer.
Pour half of the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Add remaining batter over the cinnamon.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Drain fruit and save liquid.
Take liquid, and water to equal 3 cups.
Cook pudding in this liquid until it boils and is thick.
Add gelatine to hot mixture and stir well.
Add fruit, put in serving dishes and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together first, then add beaten eggs, melted oleo and the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: stromboli
directions: Let dough rise in a warm place.
Punch down.
Roll loaves together into one 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Layer ham and pepperoni on half of the dough lengthwise.
Sprinkle with onion and green pepper.
Top with 1/4 cup pizza sauce.
Layer Mozzarella, bologna, salami with basil, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Spread another 1/4 cup pizza sauce on top.
Fold plain half of dough over filling and seal edges.
Place on greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Brush with melted oleo.
Heat the remaining pizza sauce and serve with sliced stromboli.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Mix well.
Remove top oven rack and put into 225° oven for 5 1/2 hours.
Does not require stirring.
Put into jars and seal.

title: dill bread
directions: Combine water and yeast, let dissolve.
Mix in flour, cottage cheese and dill seed.
Let stand in warm area for 30 minutes. Knead and let stand for 20 minutes.
Place into loaf pan (greased and floured) and bake at 425° until golden brown.
Butter and salt top lightly.

title: lunch box bars
directions: Bake in preheated oven at 350°.
While warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: molded liver pate
directions: Let liverwurst and butter stand at room temperature for at least an hour.
Break liverwurst up with a fork and mash it until no lumps remain.
Add soft, sweet butter and beat until well blended.
Add bourbon and pepper.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in medium saucepan, pressing out all lumps.
Then blend in evaporated milk and whole milk.
Set over high heat.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes until sugar dissolves completely.
Set off heat.
Mix in oil and bread crumbs.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.

title: sopaipillas(fried bread)
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening and add milk to make a soft dough, just firm enough to roll.
Cover bowl and let stand for 30 to 60 minutes, then roll 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board and cut into diamond shape pieces.
Heat about 1-inch of oil in frying pan to about 370° to 380°.
Add few pieces at a time.
Turn at once so they will puff evenly.
Then turn back to brown both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with butter or honey.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: harvard beets
directions: After beets are sliced, mix together sugar, flour, water, vinegar and salt. Add to the beets; cook until thick over low heat. Add butter or bacon grease.

title: tenderloin marinade
directions: Marinate meat overnight.
Turn meat after 8 hours.
Roast at 400° until desired doneness.

title: oriental green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 can French fried onions; pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: summer tea
directions: Bring 1 quart to boil and pour over tea bags.
Remove from heat.
Cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Serve over ice.
Yield: 9 cups.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Coat 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
Layer pecans, coconut in pan.
Mix cake according to instructions and pour over coconut.
Mix butter, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla. Pour over cake batter and swirl.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mother's pie dough
directions: Cut lard into flour and salt thoroughly.
Sprinkle water on top and knead gently together.
Will make one complete pie crust and one shell.

title: date pudding
directions: Place 1 cup brown sugar in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Pour boiling water over sugar.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Drop mixture in sugar and water by spoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients; microwave at High setting for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Mix both packages pudding with 3 cups cold milk.
When thick, fold in whipped topping. Pour into pan.
Spread over graham crackers.
Add another layer of whole graham crackers.
Melt chocolate with margarine.
Blend in powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons milk. Spread on top of graham crackers.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: individual brownie alaska
directions: Bake brownies as directed on package.
Cut into 3-inch squares; place on baking sheet.
Top each with small scoop ice cream and place in freezer 1 hour.
Heat oven to 500°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Cover brownies and ice cream with meringue, sealing it to edge of brownies.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes or until meringue is light brown.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Break up the pretzels.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl with a lid.
Add the pretzels and shake the bowl until the mix is all over the pretzels.
Put the pretzels in the broiler and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
They're ready to eat after cooling off.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and egg yolks in small mixer bowl at high speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix thoroughly into butter mixture.
Pat dough evenly into greased 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until light brown, about 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack 10 minutes.

title: round steak baked in oven
directions: Place in baking pan 2 pats of margarine, 1/2 envelope of onion soup, round steak, 2 pats of margarine on top of steak and 1/2 envelope onion soup.
Cover with tinfoil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kris kringles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg yolk, orange and lemon peel and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Stir in flour and salt.
Form small balls about 1/2 inch in diameter.
Dip in egg white and roll in nuts.
Press half a cherry in center.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon butter chicken
directions: Melt
butter and combine with other ingredients.
Place chicken
pieces
in
a
Dutch oven and cover with the mixture. Bake
slowly
at 150° for approximately 2 hours.
This step of slow oven cooking works for any grilled chicken recipe to make the chicken
extremely
tender.
Place
chicken pieces on the grill for
to
minutes
or until brown.
My husband's family owned
a chicken business and when the family gathered for dinner, this was the recipe they cooked most often.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients in order listed. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: polynesian treat
directions: Heat pineapple and vanilla to boiling in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Chill until thickened.
Chill milk in refrigerator tray until soft ice crystals form around edges of tray.
Whip until stiff.
Add lemon juice; whip until very stiff.
Fold into marshmallow mixture.
Combine gingersnaps and butter.
Press half of gingersnap mixture in bottom of
a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or a 9-inch pie plate.
Top with half of canned milk mixture. Repeat layers. Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: diet italian sauced fish
directions: Arrange fish in single layer on well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix sauce and onion.
Pour over fish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts, about 3 minutes.
Calories per serving:
Yield:
8 servings.

title: noodles ole
directions: Cook noodles.
While noodles cook, brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain grease from meat and add the corn, tomato soup, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer meat mixture. In a large casserole dish, alternate layers of noodles and meat mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth; cook and stir constantly until mixture boils. Cook for 1 minute; remove from heat and set aside.
In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil; season to taste with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer potatoes and onion.
Pour broth mixture over.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour; uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
If desired, sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cover potatoes with water and cook until tender.
Potatoes may be sliced before or after cooking.
Fry bacon until nice and crispy.
Take bacon out of pan but leave drippings.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Stir and cook until thickened and smooth. Remove from heat and stir in vinegar and water.
Return to stove and boil 1 minute while stirring.
Crumble in reserved bacon.
Add sliced potatoes.
Serve warm.
Also good leftover cold.

title: olivia's crab squares
directions: Cut crusts off bread and cut each slice into 4 pieces.
Mix all, but cheese, together and spread on bread.
Sprinkle top with cheese and broil until bubbly and brown.
Serve hot.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with cocoa. Place all ingredients, except chocolate chips, in large bowl and beat 2 minutes. Mix in chips. Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: spinach rice
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except pimento; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with pimento.
Makes 5 cups or 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip (2)
directions: Mix ingredients together, chill & serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Layer 1/2 cabbage, 1/2 beef, 1/2 cabbage and other 1/2 beef in buttered casserole.
Mix soup with water and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° until cabbage is tender.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Add garlic, green pepper, onion, celery and noodles to reserved broth.
Cook until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add chicken and soup.
Put in a baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/8-inch thick slices.
On waxed paper, mix flour with salt and pepper.
Coat tomatoes with mixture and let sit 15 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: In skillet brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Stir in pizza sauce, undrained mushrooms, oregano and garlic salt.
Bring to boiling; remove from heat.
Combine rotini and milk.
In 2-quart casserole layer half each of meat sauce, rotini mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish. Crumble crackers and mix with butter.
Spoon over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scald milk, oil and McButter.
Add corn meal, stirring or mixing until blended well.
Add in the eggs, mix well.
Pour into a glass baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam, or lightly greased with oil.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and apples.
Mix with orange juice and ground orange rind.
Add pineapple (juice and all).
To each cup of fruit mixture add 1/2 cup sugar.
May add nuts if you prefer.
