title: pepper steak
directions: Dice green peppers into 1-inch squares.
Dice onion.
Flash fry meat, cut into 1-inch cubes (2 1/2 minutes on each side). Season steak with black pepper (heavily).
Put in crock-pot all ingredients. Cook on low 12 hours.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Cut butter into cake mix.
Reserve 1 cup mixture for topping. Pat remaining mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan, building up 1/2-inch edge.
Spread pie filling over cake mixture to within 1/2-inch of pan edge.
Blend nuts and remaining cake mixture, sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cocktail bread sticks
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, mustard and butter.
Unroll dough.
Cut in half crosswise and then cut each in half lengthwise.
Separate strips and twist each slightly.
Place on baking sheet.
Generously brush with mustard mixture.
Makes 32 sticks.

title: aunt marie's gingersnaps
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add molasses, then egg and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Roll in small balls, then dip in sugar and place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° to 375° for 12 minutes.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Put in heavy saucepan and boil to soft ball stage (234°). Pour in 1 1/2 quarts of pecan halves.
Stir and beat as much as possible until it starts turning sugary.
Pour out on cookie sheet to cool.
Try to separate as much as possible.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion, lemon juice, salt, pepper, almonds and mayo.
Press half of mixture into large casserole or Corning Ware dish.
Cover with half sliced eggs.
Top with remaining chicken and eggs.
Top with soup, then top with chips. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican chicken manicotti
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook manicotti as directed on package; drain.
Mix chicken, carrots, Ricotta cheese, onion, cilantro and garlic.
Fill shells with mixture.
Arrange shells in an ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour salsa over manicotti. Sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese.
Cover and bake 35 minutes or until hot in center.
Makes 4 servings.
Calories: 305 per serving (11 fat grams).

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add oil and sugar and vanilla.
Stir in melted chocolate and grated zucchini.
Beat in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: banana fritters
directions: Mash bananas to a pulp.
Beat egg and sugar together.
Add bananas, then flour.
Fry in hot oil, dropping by spoonfuls in hot pan.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar, if desired.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine boiling water and Jell-O until dissolved.
In separate bowl, combine strawberries, pineapple, bananas and walnuts.
Fold into gelatin.
Spread 1/2 mixture in 12 x 8 x 2-inch or 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water for 7 minutes; drain.
Place macaroni in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Then cut cheese in small cubes.
Mix in macaroni; stir well with 1/2 cup ketchup.
Pour milk to slightly cover macaroni.
Place a few slice of cheese and 2 tablespoons of ketchup.
Bake in 350° preheated oven until done to specifications.
Makes 4 servings.
Can increase.

title: cheese filled rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
Flatten roll dough and seal perforations; cut each can of dough into 8 rectangles.
Spread about 1 tablespoon cream cheese mix on each rectangle.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Using Basic Sweet Roll Dough, roll or pat dough into long, narrow sheet about 1/4 inch thick and 6 inches wide.
Brush with melted margarine.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and nuts if desired. Beginning at long side, roll up like jelly roll.
Pinch sides together.
With a sharp knife cut into 1 inch thick slices.
Place in greased pan.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
While hot, glaze with confectioner sugar icing.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in chunks (do not peel).
Cook zucchini and chopped onion in salted water 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in shredded carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.

title: mochaccino milkshake
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: half a pound cake
directions: Cream butter (at room temperature) and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites with baking powder; fold into mixture.
Bake in 325° oven in a tube pan lined on the bottom with greased wax paper for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This may also be baked in 2 bread pans for 45 minutes, if preferred.

title: squash-eggplant casserole
directions: Wash squash with
brush.
Cut
up
and	peel
eggplant. Boil together until
done.
Drain
and
mash well with masher. Add butter, cheese, eggs and milk.
Beat well and add the rest of ingredients.
Bake	in
clear
glass dish for 45 minutes or longer until brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: fruit stick cookies
directions: Mix like bread dough (it is very stiff).
Roll in finger size rolls and press down.
Bake at 350° until done, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream well.
Drain Mandarin oranges and add to mixture.
Add marshmallows and shredded coconut and mix well.
Place in refrigerator and chill until ready to serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water and sugar together and heat on medium-low heat.
Add cornstarch to mixture when all sugar has dissolved.
Stir in strawberry Jell-O and cook over medium heat until thick.
Turn heat off and set mixture aside to let cool and to let it thicken. Place sliced strawberries in cooked pie crust.
Pour mixture over sliced berries.
Chill for several hours, then top with Cool Whip.

title: beef barbecue sauce
directions: You will also need 1 pound charcoal briquets for fire.

title: cake
directions: Put everything together, then cook it in the oven at 400° for 4 minutes.
Take it out.
Let it cool for 2 minutes.
Eat it.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar together.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Take out 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Add to remaining crumbs, the next 4 ingredients in the order they are listed.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle reserved cup of crumbs over top. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet kugel
directions: Use skim milk and low-fat ingredients.
Add about 2 teaspoons extra sugar if you do.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and dry ingredients.
Add milk, Bran and additional raisins.
Store in covered container in refrigerator. Dough will keep up to 3 weeks.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: good pork roast
directions: Cook slow until meat gets done and then take out of sauce. Let sauce continue to boil until it is as thick as you want it. Then pour over meat and serve.

title: the "ah!"  salad
directions: Cook bacon until brown and crispy.
Remove.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Place the romaine lettuce on plate.
Arrange the vegetables, turkey and cheese into long strips on top of the romaine lettuce.
The cabbage should be set in one long strip through the center.
Garnish with the bacon.
Serve with French dressing.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Combine bell peppers, jalapenos, sugar and vinegar in a saucepan.
Add food coloring.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and add Certo.
Return to heat until boiling point is reached; remove.
Add lime juice.
Pour into sterilized jars, stirring often to distribute peppers.
Pour melted paraffin on top of jars to seal.

title: holiday butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Chill.
Roll out the dough.
Use cookie cutters and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool and be sure to frost the cookies.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Blend blueberries in blender.
In large bowl, combine blueberries, sugar, marshmallow cream and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Put in freezer and serve frozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add pineapple juice to cranberry sauce.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in cream and nuts. Chill until firm.

title: sauerkraut-pork supreme
directions: Dredge pork cubes in flour and brown in oil.
Brown onions. Add sauerkraut and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Add green pepper and sour cream.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: paprika baked chicken
directions: About 1 hour before serving (on waxed paper), mix flour, salt and paprika.
Coat chicken pieces with flour mixture.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish in 425° oven, melt margarine.
Remove baking dish from oven.
Arrange chicken, skin side down in single layer in margarine.
Bake 25 minutes.
Turn pieces over.
Bake 15 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 645 calories.

title: fat-free fruit smoothie
directions: Place juice, frozen or fresh banana and fruit of your choice in blender.
Liquify.
Add ice cubes and blend until you reach shake consistency.
Makes 1 large or 2 small smoothies.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill about 1 hour.
Enjoy with vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat(serves 50)
directions: Brown beef in skillet or oven with 3 tablespoons salt.

Drain off fat; set aside. In large kettle, combine tomatoes, onion, 2 teaspoons salt, garlic powder, oregano and red pepper. Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Add bell pepper, cheese and meat. Cook 15 minutes longer or until pepper is tender.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; cut in eighths.
Arrange in unbaked pie shell. Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix second 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut in butter or oleo until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable clam chowder
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese and clams, in a large pot and cover with water; bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer until potatoes are soft (approximately 1 hour).
Remove from heat and add cheese and clams.
Reheat until cheese is melted.
Serves 12.
Can be frozen.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese and sugar until well blended, about 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and eggs; continue to beat until blended.
Place cupcake liners in cupcake pans.
Place wafer cookies, flat side down, in cupcake liners.
Fill liners with mixture to 1/4-inch from top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool on rack.
When cool, spoon cherry pie filling over tops.
Refrigerate.
Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl until oranges are broken and batter is smooth.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (one flat pan, 35 to 40 minutes).
Let cool completely and frost.

title: graham bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Thoroughly blend shortening, sugar, salt, molasses, milk and graham flour; cool.
Stir in egg and yeast; add white flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Knead well on a lightly floured surface.
Place in a greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Let rise until doubled. Shape into loaves; place in well-greased loaf pans.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, onion, red cabbage, olives and cheese in large non-metallic container.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar in a mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Add bananas, vanilla and pecans.
Add dry ingredients; mix well. Spoon into greased 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: special almquist chicken breasts
directions: Prepare grapes, walnuts and mushrooms and set to the side. Clean chicken and remove all fat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute chicken breasts in olive oil until browned on both sides.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle grapes, walnuts and mushrooms over chicken.
Drain excess oil from frying pan (but leave browned bits).
Add wine and cook down about halfway on medium-high heat. Add sour cream and stir until bubbling and smooth.
Pour over chicken and bake, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over wild rice.
Serves 4.

title: deep-dish brownie
directions: Blend butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl. Add eggs and beat.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together;
add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla and coconut after filling is done.

title: french apple coffee cake
directions: Mix 1 cup white sugar, 1 cup brown sugar, sour milk, eggs, flour, baking soda, 2 teaspoons cinnamon and salt.
Fold in apple pie filling and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cold pizza
directions: I chop all my vegetables fine and mix them in a mixing bowl (except tomato), then spread them over crust.
Add tomato, then add cheese last.

title: pink lady cake
directions: Add all the ingredients and beat well.
Put in three layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into egg mixture; mix well. Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour. Cool, then cut.

title: veal marsala
directions: Cut veal in small pieces.
Flatten with a mallet to tenderize. Dredge in flour with salt and pepper added.
Saute in frying pan in butter and oil.
Remove to plate.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Melt butter; add onion and broccoli.
Cook until tender; add soup and Cheez Whiz.
When cheese melts, add hot mixture to cooked rice.
Pour in dish; top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: molasses cake with lemon sauce(heritage)
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add molasses, shortening and eggs.
Mix well in mixer.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Beat for one minute. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan or 2 loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, broth, soup and seasonings.
Add drained peas and carrots and mushrooms.
Heat slowly, stirring occasionally, until bubbly hot.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange biscuits on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Serves six.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare the pudding with 1 cup less of milk.
Mix together pudding, milk and 1/2 of Cool Whip.

title: french fried liver
directions: Cut liver in strips in the shape of French fries.
Mix cornmeal, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper together.
Place in a plastic bag.
Add liver and shake to coat liver evenly.
Fry in deep fat.
Drain on paper towels.
Try it, you'll like it!

title: elephant stew
directions: Skin and cut elephant into 1-inch cubes.
This should take about 3 weeks.
Put into a pot and simmer over a kerosene fire about 3 months.
Add vegetables to suit your taste.
After simmering, make gravy from broth.
This will serve 3,800 people. If you happen to have a few extra show up, throw in a couple of rabbits, but do this only in an emergency!
Most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: surprise supper casserole
directions: Cook, drain and set aside the macaroni.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Alternate layers of macaroni and corned beef mixture in a 2-quart casserole baking dish (which has been sprayed with Pam).
Spread buttered bread crumbs over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Check during the last 15 minutes of baking to make sure it doesn't get too brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Put
dry yeast in the 1/4 cup water to soften.
Heat the buttermilk, sugar and shortening until the sugar is melted.
Do not
boil.
Pour
in bowl; add part of the flour and stir well. Add
the
softened
yeast;
stir until blended well and add the remainder
of the flour.
Knead until well mixed.
Sometimes it takes more than the 5 cups of flour.
Do not make the dough too stiff.
Roll
out.
Makes about 90 (2-inch) party biscuits to a batch of dough.
The biscuits can be frozen for further use.

title: dump it cake
directions: Put ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan as listed.
Do not stir. Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until tender in small amount of boiling, salted water.
Drain cabbage and save liquid.
Melt shortening in saucepan, gradually add flour, stirring constantly.
Add milk.

title: vermicelli
directions: Brown ground sirloin and onions.
Cook noodles, grate cheese, drain meat and drain noodles.
Mix meat and noodles.
Mix in tomatoes.
Mix in cheese and season to taste.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the rest of ingredients.
If desired, add 1/2 cup nuts or raisins.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Allspice or pumpkin spice can be used in place of the cinnamon.

title: linguini and clams
directions: Cook pasta; set aside.
Heat butter and add garlic.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in flour and juice from clams.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Add clams, parsley and dill; simmer 5 minutes, stirring.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.

title: billy's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion together.
Drain before putting in crock-pot.
Put drained mixture in crock-pot with pork and beans, Campbell's barbecue beans, catsup, barbecue sauce, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir all together and cook on low in crock-pot for at least 2 hours.
Longer doesn't hurt.

title: african beef stew
directions: Heat oil in a large, preferably nonstick skillet. Stir in onions and cook over medium-high heat 4 to 5 minutes until translucent.
Add beef and cook 5 minutes, stirring with a fork to break up chunks, or until browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in broth, peanut butter, tomato paste, salt and red pepper until well blended (mixture will thicken).
Stir in squash, reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes until
squash is hot.
Uncover and simmer 5 minutes longer for flavors to blend.

title: poultry with sage dressing
directions: Mix bread cubes, sage, salt, onion, celery and nuts.
Beat eggs; add 1/2 cup warm water.
Pour over mixture.
Mix well. Perhaps add 1/4 teaspoon lemon pepper or single slice of lemon; dice the rind.
If fresh bread, don't pack bird firmly.

title: jello icebox cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries to hot mix; stir until melted and starts to congeal.
After it has congealed, whip Dream Whip.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into your jello.

title: baked fish roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in small skillet.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Stir in bread crumbs, basil, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on fish fillets; roll up.
Place seam side down in 8-inch baking dish.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon melted margarine over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve with tartar sauce or lemon wedges.
Makes 2 servings.

title: ring around the skillet
directions: Cut round steak into 2 x 3-inch pieces; set aside.
Shred cabbage after washing, set aside.
Peel and cut thin slices of potatoes and set aside.
Slice onion thin and set aside.
Drain tomatoes in a stainer over a bowl.
Without mashing the tomatoes, squeeze out the seeds over the strainer.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown ground turkey or beef.
In large saucepan, bring to boil water to cook peppers for 5 minutes (peppers have had the tops cut off, chop up tops to add to the cooked meat, without stems).
Remove peppers from water, drain and salt insides.
Add to browned meat the tomatoes, onion, chopped pepper tops, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion and etc. are soft.
Add 1/8 pound Velveeta cheese (sliced up) to meat mixture and Minute rice.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Fill the peppers to top and use remaining Velveeta to top the filled peppers.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, celery, onion and pimento with salt until tender.
Put in large baking dish.
Cook milk and flour until smooth.
Add cheese and margarine; stir until melted.
Pour sauce over cabbage.
Place bread crumbs on top.
Cover with lid or foil. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf crown salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into 4 1/2 cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold, surround with lettuce.
Fill center.

title: jim fankhanel's oyster stew
directions: Simmer oysters and liquid in margarine for 3 minutes or until edges begin to curl. Scald milk in separate pan over very low heat or in double boiler. Add oysters liquid and seasonings. Serve hot; do not boil!

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pour this mixture in a greased sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips as evenly as possible on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pie is done when top is golden brown and knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: pear honey
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add pears. Process until finely chopped.
Do not puree.
Measure pears to equal 4 cups.
Combine 4 cups pears, pineapple and remaining ingredients in a heavy saucepan; bring slowly to a boil.
Cook, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring frequently, 40 minutes or until thick.
Spoon mixture into hot sterilized jars, filling to 1/4-inch from top; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands. Process in boiling-water bath 5 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack. Store in a cool, dark place.
Yield:
3 half pints.

title: hot sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and mix for about 1 minute. Store in a jar in the refrigerator. Will keep for about 2 weeks.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix Veg-All, tomato sauce, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Set aside. Tear bread into small pieces.
Mix in the eggs. Add ground chuck and soup mix.
Put in crock-pot.
Pour sauce over meat loaf.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: marinades for meats
directions: Heat and pour over meatballs.

title: sweet basil dressing(for all green salads and vegetable salads.)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a jar. Cover and allow to stand at room temperature (not cold) so flavors mix. Toss with greens or vegetables.

title: praline yams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place drained yams in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until mushy; drain.
Add all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup crumbs and a small amount of margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese, cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Prepare pie shell and cool.
Heat oven to 400°.
In blender, blend eggs and juice.
Add sweetened milk and whip.
Pour into pie shell and bake 7 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: crabmeat and artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Place in square baking dish.
Bake at 400° until heated and slightly browned.

title: corn pudding(serves 8)
directions: Mix ingredients well; put in 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Bake in moderate oven until firm.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler. Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Add nuts and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: candied nuts
directions: Bake the pecans at 250° for 8
minutes. Bring to a rapid boil the sugar, water, vanilla and cinnamon. Put nuts in cooked mixture and spread on a lightly greased cookie sheet and cool.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Line cupcake pan with liners.
Place a vanilla wafers in each liner.
Beat together, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, eggs and lemon juice.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 15 minutes in 375°F. oven. Cool and spoon pie filling over each tart.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Can be made a day ahead.
Makes 18-20 tarts.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease pie pan with butter. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond flavoring.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well.

title: (uncooked) figs
directions: Mix crushed fruit and Sure-Jell and let stand 20 minutes.
Add Karo syrup and stir well.
Add sugar and stir thoroughly.
Place in containers and freeze.
Good on biscuits, toast or as a topping for ice cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well and add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in loaf pans or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: lazy-way beef burgundy
directions: Place beef cubes, onion, wine and consomme in a 2 1/2 qt. casserole.
Mix flour and bread crumbs together; add to casserole. Stir all ingredients together until completely blended. Cover.
Bake at 325 degrees for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until meat is tender...stirring once every hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Melt margarine in small oblong Pyrex dish. Cook apples a few minutes; sweeten as desired. Pour in buttered dish. Pour flour mixture across apples in strips. Bake at 375° until top is brown.

title: heath bar ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla. Add chocolate bits. Pour in freezer and freeze.
Makes 1 quart.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Place
all
dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Mix with all other ingredients;	pour in an ungreased single cake pan 9 x 13-inch
size.
Bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Mix by hand only.)

title: chicago public school lunch room butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with electric mixer until light and creamy. Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar until the dough isn't grainy.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Add vanilla.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Pour sugar on plate and press 2 fingers into sugar and then onto cookie to flatten.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: deer stew
directions: Brown meat; cut into pieces in bacon fat.
Add 2 large onions, sliced.
Continue browning.
When nicely browned, stir in 3 tablespoons flour.
Place in baking dish and add vinegar, catsup, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover meat with water and bake at 375° for 2 to 3 hours or until tender, adding water as needed to keep meat covered.
When done, thicken gravy and serve.

title: brown sugar custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and cornstarch, then add butter, milk and vanilla. (Use wooden spoon or whisk, not electric mixer.) Cover bottom of unbaked pie crust with pecans or raisins; pour pie mixture in pie crust and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 275°; bake until firm.

title: peanut-mallow light fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, syrup and milk.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, margarine, peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pan.

title: mexican cherry cobbler
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass casserole, place flour tortillas rolled up with cherry pie filling.
In each saucepan, cook oleo with water, sugar, red coloring and almond flavoring.
Bring to boil and pour over top of tortillas.
Let set 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray baking sheet lightly with Baker's Joy.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies (they will look light and moist) or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: hearty pork soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat oil; add pork, garlic and onions; cook and stir until meat is cooked through.
Add remaining ingredients except rotelle; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Prepare rotelle as package directs and drain.
Stir into soup.
Heat through.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: red hot candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until it reaches hard-crack stage.
Add cinnamon oil and food coloring.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.
Remove from pan and break into small pieces.
Store tightly sealed.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Combine pecans, brown sugar and flour.
Beat eggs, add butter.
Mix well.
Add to dry mixture.
Stir till just moistened. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 9 muffins.

title: chopped coins
directions: Cook carrots approximately 20 minutes, until just tender.
Mix carrots, onion and green pepper.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together until done.
Add chili powder, mustard, catsup and soup.
Simmer until real thick, about 1 hour on medium heat.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients, mixing in pieces of Butterfinger.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.

title: mother's tea cakes
directions: Mix.
Roll thin and cut.
Bake in medium oven until light brown.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and sour cream to which the soda has been added.
Mix in bananas, vanilla, flour and salt. Bake in jelly roll pan at 375° for 30 minutes.
Ice with Powdered Sugar Icing.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Chill.
Garnish with bacon just before serving.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Beat cream cheese and mayo.
Add to lemon Jell-O mix.
Add undrained pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Chill 1 hour, until firm.
Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Add pie filling and spoon over top of lemon Jell-O mixture.
Chill until set.

title: aunt alice's stromboli
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise. Spread tomato sauce on both sides of the bread. Fry sausage and drain grease, then put on bread. Cut up pieces of onion and green pepper and scatter over sausage. Scatter pepperoni over everything and then cover with Mozzarella cheese. Cover the bread with other piece of bread. Wrap loosely with foil. Bake at 350° until cheese melts. If top of bread gets hard, sprinkle a little water on top of bread and put back in oven for a few minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix flour and baking powder together.
Combine sugar and flour mixtures.
Blend.
Add pineapple, mix to combine.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into 20 slices.

title: hawaiian butterscotch cookies
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder and salt to flour.
Blend. Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Add dry ingredients to the mixture. Stir in butterscotch morsels, pineapple and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: buttercream decorating icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening together with an electric mixer. Add vanilla and salt.
Beat in sugar, one cup at a time, blending well after each addition.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often with a spatula.
Add milk and beat at high speed for 10 minutes. Keep icing covered with lid and store in refrigerator.
Chill before making roses.
To use as frosting, thin with milk.
Yields 3 cups.
It can also be frozen.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook in slow cooker until thickens.

title: crock pot steak and gravy
directions: Do not trim meat.
Place in 4 - 5 quarts crock pot.
Sprinkle with onion-mushroom soup mix and 1/2 cup Water.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
After cooking, remove steak and keep warm.
Remove juices to sauce pan, add hot Water and Corn Starch.
Cook on medium-high, stirring constantly with a whisk until gravy thickens and starts to bubble.
Serves 4.

title: summer sausage
directions: Peel onion, leaving root end intact.
Cut onion vertically into quarters, cutting to within 1/2-inch of root end.
Cut each quarter vertically into thirds.
Place onion in boiling water 1 minute; remove and place in ice water 5 minutes.
Loosen petals if necessary.
Drain onion, cut side down.
Place flour in a zip-top plastic bag; add onion, shaking to coat.
Dip onion in egg.
Place cracker crumbs in plastic bag; add onion, tossing to coat.
Chill 1 hour.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand 1 hour.
Boil last 3 ingredients for 1 minute; cool and pour over cabbage.
Great for freezing.

title: avocado tostado salad
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add chili beans with juice, salt and chili powder.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: saucy franks
directions: Score franks in corkscrew fashion.
In skillet, brown franks lightly in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except green pepper.
Simmer, covered, about 10 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook, covered, 5 minutes more.
Serve over hot cooked noodles or over buns.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together in a bowl.
Let stand refrigerated for at least 12 hours.

title: lake charles dip
directions: Mix together. Chill. Serve with vegetable sticks.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: Place peanut butter chips, milk and whipping cream in a medium-sized microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes; stir.
If necessary, microwave on High an additional 30 seconds at a time, stirring after each heating, until chips are melted when stirred.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream. Mmmmmmmmm! Refrigerate leftovers, if any.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour until browned.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Cube chicken breasts.
Saute the onion, green pepper and chicken in the oil.
Cook until chicken is cooked.
Add corn, chicken broth and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Add the Minute rice. Stir; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff up, then sprinkle on the cheese.
Cover for 2 more minutes until the cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Combine cooked zucchini or squash, sour cream, chicken soup, chopped raw onion, carrot, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm seasoned dressing, dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy beer chili
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in Dutch oven; remove and crumble. Brown beef in drippings.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Add crumbled bacon; simmer for 15 minutes more.
Serve with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: mom's meatloaf
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Place in 6 x 9 x 1-inch pan. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
Drain excess grease.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Mix together onion, butter, celery seed, paprika and garlic salt. Put potatoes in crock-pot. Fill 3/4 full. Pour all other ingredients over potatoes. Add water if needed.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Blend in well beaten egg.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and add to mixture, alternately, with sour cream.
Blend in flavoring.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar, 1/4 cup sugar to 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, chocolate pudding with cold milk; whip. Pour over layer 1.

title: lemon dessert(makes 20 servings.  prep time:  20 minutes.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine. Add flour and pecans. Mix well and spread in 9 x 13 baking dish.

Press into dish with butter coated fingers. Should be thick enough to handle and about 1/4-inch thick in pan. If you don't have enough dough, make more. Bake for about 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; add onions, mushroom soup and cheese. Mix well.
Pour into a baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Put this mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Top with soup, then cheese, then Tater Tots.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes brown and cheese bubbles.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour boiling water into corn meal.
Add Crisco; stir in well beaten eggs, milk and salt.
Pour into lightly greased casserole. Bake at 400° about 1 hour, or until delicately brown.

title: pecan delights
directions: Mix together, Quaker Oat Squares & pecans, in a 9 X 13 inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients in microwavable bowl and cook to a boil about 2 minutes.
Pour over oat squares and mix thoroughly. Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1 layer cake in punch bowl. Add 1/2 pudding mix, 1/2 pie filling and 1/2 pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts. Repeat each layer.

title: scallops
directions: Rinse scallops and dredge in flour.
Heat butter in a heavy skillet and brown scallops.
Set aside to keep warm.
In the same pan, slowly add scotch and vermouth, stirring to make a smooth roux.
Add 1/4 cup cream, if desired, to make a smooth sauce. Spoon over scallops.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Work together with fingers.
Top and bake 20 more minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 can French fried onions. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions, bake uncovered 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated grilled chicken breasts
directions: Combine soy sauce, lemon juice and garlic in a Ziploc bag. Add chicken breasts.
Marinate for 2 hours or overnight.
Grill 2 inches from hot coals for 8 minutes on each side or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: mushroom sandwich filling
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce while cooking.
Add heavy cream and salt to taste.
Thicken mixture with flour, adding additional flour, if needed. Refrigerate.
This filling is best made the day before using.

title: peach velvet upside down cake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons oleo in 9-inch round pan, add brown sugar. Arrange peach slices and cherry halves in pan.
In a small bowl mix Bisquick, sugar, oleo, egg and vanilla.
Continue beating 1/2 minute.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Invert at once onto serving dish (allow pan to remain over cake a few minutes to allow sugar mixture to run down over cake).
Serve warm, plain or with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Chill thoroughly before using.

title: apple dump cake
directions: In an oblong Pyrex dish, spread pie filling.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar.
Spread cake mix on top, then top with pecans. Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until bubbling and brown.

title: barbecue joes(microwave)
directions: To brown meat, crumble ground beef in a microwave-safe dish. Add vegetables.
Cover and cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring once.

title: low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Combine the first 4 ingredients in a small bowl and set aside.
In mixer bowl, mix sugar and Butter Buds.
Add water to sugar mixture and beat until well mixed.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to egg mixture at slow speed.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stove top meat loaf
directions: Chop onion, pepper and celery finely.
Mix all ingredients except soup.
Shape into 2 rounded loaves.
(Add an egg if it seems dry or more bread crumbs if it's too wet when you shape it, depending on the amount of ground beef.)
Spray a large skillet with cooking spray and heat on medium.
Brown the loaves on each side for a total of about 10 minutes.
Pour in a can of soup and a can of water.
Reduce heat to low and cook for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch in saucepan.
Boil until thick and clear.
While hot, add jello.
Place 1 quart fresh strawberries into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Then pour glaze over strawberries and chill.

title: super skillet nachos
directions: In large skillet, brown beef with onions; drain the liquid. Add the 2 cups picante sauce, beans and chili powder and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in the tomato and olives.
Remove from heat and sprinkle the shredded cheese over the top.
Spoon sour cream onto the center of the meat mixture.
Place a row of tortilla chips around the edge of the skillet and serve immediately with additional chips and picante sauce.

title: holiday ham sauce
directions: In medium size glass bowl, combine raisins, water, jelly and orange juice.
Heat in microwave on High power for 3 minutes, stirring after 1 1/2 minutes of cooking.
In separate bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch and allspice.
Stir mixture; blend into raisin mixture.
Cook in microwave on High power for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes until thickened, stirring every 30 seconds.
Serve over ham, pork chops or duck.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Grease pan.
Brown sausage and onion; drain well.
Combine eggs, cornmeal, milk and oil.
Pour half of cornmeal mixture into dish.
Sprinkle with sausage mixture and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Cook at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute in olive oil the onions, peppers and garlic.
Remove from heat.
Brown meat and drain grease.
To meat add sauteed mix. Add 2 cans of stewed, crushed tomatoes.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Add brown sugar, baked beans and chili powder to taste. Simmer.

title: mussel stew
directions: Put mussels in ice water and throw out any that do not close. While soaking mussels, saute onions until transparent. Add wine. When boiling add mussels. When mussels are open (throw out any unopened ones) pour into bowels, serve with bread.

title: prune apple cake
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs 2 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients; gradually mix into egg mixture.
Mix in prunes, apples and nuts at low speed to blend thoroughly.
Spoon into buttered and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Smooth top.

title: pralines(candy)
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugars are dissolved.
Continue cooking over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool and beat until it begins to thicken.
Add pecans; mix well and drop rapidly with tablespoon on waxed paper or foil.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Crust:
Mix well, roll thin and cut into strips.
Line bottom and sides of bowl with strips and add alternately with layers of fruit filling.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together when room temperature.
Chill, then roll in nuts.

title: microwave stuffing
directions: Combine mushrooms, onion, celery and margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High (100%) until vegetables are tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave at High (100%) until heated through, 4 to 7 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients (except margarine) together.
Have pork chops moist.
Lightly salt and pepper before turning over in mixture.
Line baking dish with foil and spray with Pam.
Place chops on foil and drizzle margarine on top.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes or until done (lightly brown).

title: marshmallow sweet potato casserole
directions: Pare and cut potatoes into chunks.
Cook in pineapple juice until tender.
Drain and reserve syrup.
Mash potatoes, add reserved syrup and remaining ingredients (except marshmallows) and mix well.
Put mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Lightly press marshmallows into top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies no. 3
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream, in a large bowl, the sugar, brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Set aside.
In a medium size bowl, mix together the flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 9 dozen.

title: cucumber sauce(serve with tuna or salmon loaf)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: crab puffs
directions: Combine crab meat, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Blend well.
Add cream cheese.
Mix until smooth.
Place a scant 1/2 tablespoon of crab mixture in wonton wrapper.
Brush edges of wrapper with egg white.
Fold wonton diagonally to form a triangle.
Seal edges. Again brush edges with egg white.
Join all corners of the triangle and crimp together.
Deep fry in salad oil, heated to 375°, for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain well after browning evenly. Serve hot.
Makes 20 puffs.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute cabbage and onion in butter.
Add water, green beans, carrot and Cup-a-Soup.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serve in bowl with Muenster cheese on bottom.

title: chocolate chip surprise
directions: Pour 2 cups milk into small mixing bowl.
Quickly dip one cookie at a time in milk and place in bottom of 8 x 12-inch cake dish.
Do not hold cookies in milk for more than 1/4 second!
When bottom of cake dish is full, cover cookies with a thin layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers to fill cake dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 8.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix half of stuffing with all ingredients.
Add remaining stuffing on top of large casserole.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 10.

title: chocolate banana bobs
directions: Peel bananas.
Cut crosswise into 4 pieces.
Insert wooden ice cream stick in each piece.
Place on baking sheet.
Freeze until bananas are firm, about 2 hours.
In top of double boiler over boiling water, melt shortening and chocolate pieces, stirring occasionally.
Dip bananas into mixture, spreading over pieces. Roll in nuts.
Place on waxed paper-covered baking sheet.
Freeze until firm.
When firm, wrap each in aluminum foil.
Return to freezer.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 16 Banana Bobs.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Chill the lemon and orange juices in the freezer.
Add the milk and cream.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Freeze. Makes 3 quarts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and put into casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the potato mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hopping john soup
directions: Drain peas, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to pea liquid to make 2 cups.
Combine peas, soup mix, liquid and sausage.
Bring this mixture to a boil and reduce heat to low.
Cover tightly and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 30 minutes. Add more water or liquid, if needed.

title: my mother's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Pour into ice cream container.
Continue process in making ice cream.

title: cheese straws
directions: Add melted butter to grated cheese.
Add dry ingredients and add to cheese mixtures.
Knead well.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 18 minutes but don't brown.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Place buttermilk and baking soda in heavy 4 quart saucepan. Stir thoroughly.
Let stand five minutes.
Stir again.
Add sugar, syrup and butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Soda will cause mixture to look foamy.
Mixture will become brownish in color during the cooking process.
Cook to softball stage.
Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla.
DO NOT STIR.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat to creamy consistency and pour into buttered pan.

title: sweet-sour meatball appetizer
directions: Combine hamburger and salt into balls.
Mix together ketchup and ginger ale; bring to a slow boil.
Drop in meatballs.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours, occasionally skimming off fat that rises to top. Meatballs are ready to serve when sauce thickens.
Makes 40.

title: green beans scandia
directions: Drain liquid from beans into saucepan (1-quart or larger). Add next 6 ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Stir in cornstarch mixed with water.
Cook and continue stirring until mixture thickens and is clear, about 5 minutes.
Add cabbage; heat to boiling.
Simmer, covered, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add drained beans and cook until beans are hot.
Serve at once.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: fluffy fruit dressing
directions: Mix fruit juices.
Add eggs and sugar.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened.
Cool.
Add whipped cream.
Makes 1 quart.

title: microwave peppers with green rice
directions: Cut the top off each pepper crosswise; remove stem and dice remaining pepper top into bowl.
Remove seeds and hollow out whole peppers.
To chopped pieces in bowl, add spinach, eggs, garlic, rice, Parmesan cheese, butter and half tomato sauce.
Mix well and divide evenly into hollowed peppers.
Arrange in 2-quart casserole.
Spoon remaining half tomato sauce over peppers, cover. Microwave on High 15 to 20 minutes until heated.
Top with cheese.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt cheese,
soup and 1 stick of margarine; mix cooked rice and cooked broccoli together.
Pour melted sauce over and stir real
well.
If
desired,
add
one jar sliced mushrooms. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into a loaf.
Place in a buttered oblong baking dish.

title: apple pie(makes its own crust)
directions: In pie plate, melt margarine.
In a bowl, sift flour and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla to flour mixture.
Be sure it is mixed thoroughly.
When margarine is melted, pour flour mixture into the melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Drain apples and place them evenly on top of flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup with cucumber(feine kartoffelsuppe mit gurken; makes 6 servings)
directions: Peel the cucumber and slice it lengthwise into halves.
Scoop out the seeds and cut into 1/4-inch dice and set aside.
In a heavy 4-quart saucepan, bring the potatoes and water to a boil over high heat.
Reduce the heat to moderate.
Add the salt and pepper and cook, uncovered, until the potatoes are soft and can easily be mashed against the sides of the pan.
Then pour them and all the cooking liquid into a sieve set over a bowl.
With a large spoon, force through the sieve.
Don't use a blender, it makes the mixture too smooth.
Return the potatoes and liquid to the saucepan and stir in the cream, milk, grated onion and cucumbers. Simmer over low heat for about 5 minutes or until the cucumber is tender but still firm.
Add the dill and taste for seasoning. Serve hot.

title: mexican chicken lasagne
directions: Pour both jars of salsa into a large non-aluminum saucepan. Add the pepper, chili powder, cumin, and garlic.
Bring to a boil; reduce the heat and simmer uncovered, stirring often, until the sauce is reduced to 4 cups, about 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook the lasagne noodles according to package directions and drain well.

title: date carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in eggs.
Add pineapple, carrots, dates and vanilla, beating well.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool completely. Sprinkle top of cake with powdered sugar.

title: quick italian spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add olives; simmer 5 more minutes.
Spoon over spaghetti; sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.
This dish can be ready by the time the spaghetti is cooked.

title: delightful delectable ribs
directions: Cut ribs.
Brown in iron skillet.
Place in a pan, over medium heat.
Add soup, water, onions, Worcestershire sauce and pepper over ribs.
Cover and simmer, 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning and adding water if thick.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and egg yolks until light.
Add oil and beat.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to sugar, egg and oil mixture.
Add crushed pineapple, carrots and butter flavor.
Add nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Mix lightly through sliced apples. Heap up in unbaked pastry shell.
Dot with butter and add topping.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs.
Plunge into cold water.
Remove shells. Place in sterilized jar.
Heat vinegar and water; add seasoning. Pour over edges.
Let eggs stand for at least 1 week.
Refrigerate after opening.

title: yellow rice and shrimp
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions.
If shrimp are uncooked, drop in boiling water until pink and remove.
If precooked, prepare for use according to package instructions.

title: pumpkin waffles with warm cider syrup
directions: Beat together the buttermilk, egg yolks, oil and brown sugar. Stir in pumpkin puree until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Stir flour mixture into pumpkin mixture just until blended.
Batter does not need to be smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Bake waffles in a heated iron according to manufacturer's directions. Keep waffles warm on a rack in a 200° oven until all batter is used.
Serve waffles with Warm Apple Cider Syrup.
Yields 6 round 7-inch waffles.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Saute chopped peppers, celery, onions and garlic in margarine until glazed.
Add oysters and juice.
When oysters start to curl, add soup, hot sauce and cracker crumbs.
Put in greased casserole. Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into an oblong pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove and cool in pan.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread mixture on crust.
Top with pie filling and chill.

title: smoked gar
directions: Season gar.
Smoke 4 hours over ash or hickory.
Remove and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Melt butter and brown gar for 1 minute. Add the rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
To serve, pour desired amount of beans over rice.
Add a few pieces of gar and sauce.
Enjoy.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook noodles.
Combine all ingredients, saving 1 1/2 cups of cheese for topping.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Makes 2 large pans.

title: poppycock-popcorn
directions: In a very large bowl, mix first 3 ingredients and set aside. In a saucepan, combine the sugar, corn syrup and butter and cook to little more than soft-ball stage. Add vanilla. Pour over popcorn mixture and mix well.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour pan well.
Mix sugar and eggs well.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in four 1-pound coffee cans, halfway full.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Slice and spread cookie dough in pizza pan to cover the edges. Bake for 11 to 13 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla and sugar together.
Spread on cooled cookie dough.
Then arrange fruit.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Heat tortillas in skillet, one at a time.
Place 2 tablespoons of cheese, chicken and onion in each tortilla and roll.
Place, seam side down, in 11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Do not stir ingredients. Place crushed pineapple with juice in bottom.
Add blueberries.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over berries.
Pour cake mix over ingredients.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: karin's bread
directions: Mix in above order, adding yeast after warm water.
Add flour gradually.
Makes large amount of dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in medium size pans.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water, let cool.
Sift flour and salt together; set aside.
Cream butter.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the sugar and continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks. Blend in dry ingredients alternating with sour cream and vanilla. Dissolve soda in chocolate; stir chocolate mixture and coloring into batter.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar and continue beating until soft peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour into 2 - 8 inch round pans (lined with wax paper).
Bake at 350 for 40-45 minutes.
Frost with White Icing Recipe (do add the peanut butter).

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Mix all together well and pour into a well-greased casserole. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pound cake with raspberries
directions: Heat jam in saucepan until just melted.
Cut cake in cubes and divide among 6 dessert dishes.
Top each serving with jam, yogurt and fresh raspberries and serve immediately.

title: baked whiting
directions: Split fish lengthwise.
Place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with tomato sauce and diced onion.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flours, brown sugar, spices, baking powder and soda.
In small bowl, combine buttermilk, applesauce, molasses and eggs.
Add to flour.
Beat with electric beaters until mixed.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Do not substitute all-purpose flour for whole wheat.

title: apple cheese snack
directions: Wash apples.
Cut into quarters.
Core the apples, then cut the quarters into smaller pieces.
Place on a serving tray.
Put the cheese wedges in the center.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese slightly; gradually stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion, seasoned salt and chutney.
Chill well.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg, vanilla and zucchini together, then dry ingredients need to be added.
Drop dough onto cookie sheet. Bake at 300°.
Cookies will be soft like.
Sift powdered sugar over hot cookies.

title: chocolate gravy(for breakfast)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large saucepan.
Add milk.
Cook until the thickness of gravy.
Pour over homemade biscuits.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, combine broccoli, onion, bacon, raisins and peanuts.
In separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Pour over broccoli.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
The combination of ingredients is wonderful! Serves 4 to 6.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into buttered pie plate or casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, meat, onion and sauce. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake 15 minutes more, or until potatoes are tender. Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350° temperature.

title: victoria's salad
directions: Dressing:
In blender, blend parsley and shallot well.
Add vegetable oil, olive oil, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Blend well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and sugar.
Add eggs, meal, flour, vanilla, milk and nuts.
Fill unbaked pie shell and bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Check center to see when done.

title: crispy cornflakes cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into cornflakes mixture.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, garlic, salt, tomato sauce and ripe olives and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and chilies. Place half of meat mixture, half of sour cream mixture, layer of cheese and layer of Doritos.
Repeat.
Heat in oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pa pa's pepper steak
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add salt and pepper and cover with water.
Let boil and turn to medium heat.
Simmer.
Add dash of red crushed pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 2 tablespoons Kitchen Bouquet.
Then add the bell peppers, chopped. Cook 20 minutes and serve over rice.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in pie plate, top with chopped pepper.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds, blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: lemon and lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple and heat juice to dissolve jello.
Mix well and chill.

title: american potato salad
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: dijon marinade
directions: Remove fat.
Blend spices and then beat in oil by drop. Use a rubber spatula and paint on lamb.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix in shortening.
Add milk and yeast.
Roll out on floured surface; cut.
Dip in butter.
Place on greased baking pan.
Let rise for about 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, milk and egg together.
Dip apples into this mixture, then deep fry until brown.
Sift confectioners sugar over drained apples.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well in bowl and chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening with hand.
Beat in one egg at a time with mixer.
Add flour and milk, then vanilla and lemon. Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open door until time is up.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese sit at room temperature until soft.
Mix all ingredients together and roll into ball.
Roll ball in finely chopped pecans.
Serve at room temperature.

title: apple macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray roaster with Pam (then sprinkle bread crumbs over bottom-optional).
In salted water cook noodles; bring to boil and cook for 2 minutes from the time the water starts to boil.
Drain off water.
Rinse very well to remove starch.
Melt butter and mix into noodles.
Peel and slice apples. Mix apples with sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice.

title: orange dream pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Sift flour with salt and mix with butter mixture just until dough will form (if using electric mixer, use low speed).
Place 1/3 cup of the mixture in a small pan to use for crumb topping.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat
egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until very stiff.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks and add milk, a little at
a time.
Add
sugar,
lemon
juice,
rind, salt and lemon extract. Add
flour.
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in buttered 9
x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Set in pan of water and bake
at 300° for about 1 hour.
Cake will brown slightly when done.

title: birds nests
directions: Melt paraffin in microwave at 70% power for 2 or 3 minutes or until almost melted.
Add butterscotch and microwave another 2 or 3 minutes at 50% power.
Mix noodles and nuts into melted mixture. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, salt, pepper, onion, sour cream, cheese and half of melted butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss corn flakes with remaining butter and spread over potato mixture. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes, usually needs to be cooked an hour.
Serves 10.
Serve hot.

title: cheese pecan wafers
directions: Using an electric mixer, combine all ingredients to make a soft dough.
Divide into quarters, and roll each piece into a log about 1 inch in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper, and refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.

title: teriyaki beef ribs
directions: Separate beef ribs.
Set aside.
Heat and stir remaining ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Marinate ribs in sauce for two hours or overnight.
Next day, lift ribs from marinade, gently shaking off excess.
Barbecue, basting occasionally with remaining marinade.
Makes 6 servings.
(Sauce is also good for Teriyaki Steak.)

title: greek vegetables
directions: Clean leeks.
Discard green tops.
Cut in half lengthwise. Clean mushrooms; cut in half.
Clean zucchini; cut into 3-inch pieces and into 1/2-inch slices (also carrots and green beans).

title: baked crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered casserole dish, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good served with ham or turkey.

title: german cheesecake
directions: Blend crumbs, 1 tablespoon sugar, cinnamon and butter together.
Press in a 9-inch pie plate using smaller plate to press down.
Add egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and lemon juice to smoothly beaten cream cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into cheese mixture. Turn into crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Combine 1 teaspoon vanilla, sour cream and 3 tablespoons sugar; spread over cooled cake.
Return to oven.
Bake for 5 minutes longer. Cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pour all ingredients over carrots and refrigerate overnight.

title: salad
directions: Layer top with the Hellmann's mayonnaise and the sugar.
Cover with grated cheese.

title: pineapple nut refrigerator pie
directions: Mix well and pour in graham cracker crust; chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: berried delight
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup melted butter firmly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator pie
directions: Drain cherries; cook pineapple, cherries, flour and sugar until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add dry jello and let cool.
Add chopped bananas and nuts.
Put in graham cracker crust and let set in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: pork chops with kidney beans
directions: Wash chops and pat dry.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper, then dip in flour, covering both sides.
In large skillet, with a little oil on bottom (about 1/4 cup), brown chops on both sides.
Pour off oil; add tomato sauce and water.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans; cook 15 minutes more or until chops are done.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Melt oleo in skillet and add broccoli and onion.
Saute for 15 minutes.
Stir while cooking. Mix Cheez Whiz, soup and milk and add to broccoli.
Add together with rice.
Place in baking dish and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Note:
Light, low calorie and low salt products can be substituted.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured cake pans.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together.
Beat egg white and water until soft peaks form.
Add nuts to egg mixture and mix well.
Add sugar mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cocktail spread
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Spread in a 12-inch dish or platter.
Scatter shrimp over cheese mixture.
Add layer of seafood sauce, then cheese, onions, tomato and green pepper. Cover until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.
(Best eaten on the day it's made.)

title: linda's chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Mix together the Wesson oil, oregano, soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish and pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Baste or cover.
Serves 6.

title: apple nut cake
directions: *I used 1 1/2 teaspoons of pumpkin pie spice.
Also, the recipe says to peel the apples; I didn't.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt, all at one time; stir vigorously.
Cook, stirring constantly, on medium low heat until mixture forms ball and doesn't separate.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat hard after each addition until mixture is smooth.
Form puffs on cookie sheet, about a heaping teaspoonful (don't mash down), 2 inches apart.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° for 25 minutes.
Should be a nice, golden brown.
Take toothpick to let air out.
Take extra strings.
Fill with Cool Whip, whipped whipping cream or pudding.

title: apple cider
directions: Mix together and allow to simmer for 1 hour.

title: sweet chocolate chip muffins
directions: Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 medium muffins.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients, except almonds. Mix well.
Spoon mixture into ungreased 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: therapeutic vegetable juice
directions: Place carrot pieces in blender bowl.
Cut 1-inch off a raw celery stick and place in blender bowl.
Add garlic to blender bowl.
Add ginger powder to blender bowl.
Add cayenne pepper to blender bowl.
Place all concentrated juices and other ingredients in blender together.
Add distilled water to fill blender bowl. Blend for a few seconds.
Add Vegit (an all vegetable seasoning) as desired (optional).
Conversely, this drink may not be the most palatable, however, it is certainly therapeutic in its design.

title: after-the-holidays salad
directions: In a mixing bowl toss first 6 ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients, except lettuce leaves.
Pour over turkey mixture and mix gently.
Chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: quick spaghetti dinner
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. In a skillet, brown the beef.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and sauce mix.

Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and stir in Cheddar cheese. Return to low heat to melt cheese, if necessary. Serve over spaghetti. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and rice in greased baking dish.
Add chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with paprika.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
(Ovens vary; keep checking to make sure when chicken is done and that the rice is not becoming too dry.)
An extra can of mushrooms can be added if you like.

title: roasted corn black bean and mango salad
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic; cook 30 seconds.
Stir in corn; cook 8 minutes or until browned, stirring occasionally.
Place corn mixture in a large bowl.
Add mango and remaining ingredients except greens; stir well.
Arrange 1 cup greens on each of 8 plates.
Spoon 1 cup corn mixture over greens.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain.
Add chili beans, tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and soup.
Add chili powder to taste and simmer on low heat for 3 hours.

title: special k candy
directions: Heat in pan on stove: sugar, corn syrup.
Heat to dissolve sugar.
Off heat, add peanut butter and mix.
Add Special K cereal.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased); sprinkle with chocolate chips.
(May need to bake 3 to 5 minutes at 350° to melt chocolate.)
Spread chocolate over top.
Refrigerate.
Cut into small squares when cooled.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix the whipped milk with the sifted sugar, adding hot oleo. Add coconut and chopped nuts.
Drop onto waxed paper in medium size balls.
Let set 1 hour.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with pork loin and cracklin' bread.

title: banana split salad
directions: Make graham cracker crust with melted margarine and crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and soft margarine until light. Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat good and spread mixture over graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Add drained pineapple on top.
Slice bananas and put on top of pineapple. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Serves 14.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 2 quart casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: black cherry sparkle
directions: Drain cherries and set aside juice.
In a saucepan, melt butter and add juice from the cherries; mix well.
Add cornstarch and sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Heat, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened; remove from heat.
Add cherries and almond extract. Put cake on individual plates.
Pour sparkling cherry sauce over slices.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Set aside.
Beat eggs slightly in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened. Spoon batter into two well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: pinto beans
directions: Sort and wash beans and place them in a large pot and cover them with water.
At this point you can let them soak overnight or cook them overnight.
I prefer the latter.
Add all the other ingredients, cover pot and bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat and simmer on low heat all night or day.
Check the water and stir occasionally.

title: curried butternut squash soup
directions: Slice, peel, scoop out seeds and cut squash into bite-sized pieces.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes. Yields 8 servings.
Has 250 calories, 2 g fat.

title: cheese cake #2
directions: Follow directions for making graham cracker crust off of package.
Press firmly into a greased 8-inch cake pan (spring-form pan is best).
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve jello in yogurt. Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker pie crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: refrigerator cabbage slaw
directions: Shred or thinly slice onions and cabbage.
Combine the first 6 ingredients and bring to a full boil.
Alternate cabbage and onions in a large bowl.
Pour hot dressing over and cover tightly. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before using.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat margarine and cocoa powder until margarine is softened.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, beating well.
Slowly beat in 3 tablespoons skim milk and vanilla. Slowly beat in 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar and additional skim milk, if needed, to make of spreading consistency.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine spices, salt, pumpkin, milk and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and blend. Cook over low heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool and chill until partially thickened.
Whip egg whites with the remaining sugar.
Fold into pumpkin mix.
Turn into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach balls
directions: Blend all ingredients well. Shape into 1-inch balls and bake at 325° for 20 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Makes about 100.

title: six minute cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa together.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended (1 to 2 minutes). Mixture will be thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk and mix well. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours. Garnish with additional Cool Whip (and nuts, if desired).
Serves 8.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water about 10 minutes.
Saute leeks and onion in oil until golden.
Add to potatoes and stir in milk and seasonings.
Simmer until the flavors are blended (about 15 minutes).
Add parsley and heat almost to boiling, stirring frequently.
Enrich soup with cream and serve hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the hamburger mixture.
Put mashed potatoes on top of hamburger mixture.
Line top of potatoes with any kind of cheese to your liking.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: date strips
directions: To eggs, add all other ingredients, except only add half of package of dates.
Pour batter in 9 x 13-inch pan; press rest of dates evenly on top of batter in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar; cut into strips when cool.

title: peanut butter crispy treats(microwave)
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In 3-quart microwave dish, stir Karo syrup, sugar and peanut butter until blended.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes or until entire surface is bubbly.
Add cereal; toss to coat well.
Press into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 32 squares.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: First-layer of lettuce.
Second-layer of cauliflower. Third-crumble unthawed green peas.
Fourth-spread mayonnaise over all above ingredients, except the seasoning.
Add the seasoning mix as directed on the package to above ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on the top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: rice pudding
directions: Simmer boiling water, rice, butter and salt for 15 minutes. Add scalded milk to rice mixture and simmer 15 more minutes.
Add beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Cook for 3 to 4 more minutes. Pour into serving bowl.
Cinnamon may be sprinkled on top.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and soda to batter.
Mix well. Add sour cream and vanilla. Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Check for doneness.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add next 6 ingredients with meat.
Simmer 1 hour until thick.
Boil noodles.
