Combine cottage cheese with eggs, salt, pepper, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend together eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt and soda and add to mixture.
Add walnuts, apples and vanilla. Bake 1 hour at 350° in large oblong pan.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Do not overcook.
Cool and spread over cake.
This is excellent over ice cream for hot fudge sauce.
Double the recipe for a 9 x 13-inch loaf cake.
Cut the cake and pour the icing on cake while hot.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In saucepan, melt peanut butter and butter.
In large bowl, combine powdered sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Blend together with hands.
Form into 1/2-inch balls.
Chill until firm.
Melt butterscotch pieces and chocolate pieces in separate double boilers.
Dip half the candies in each coating; swirl tops with back of teaspoon.
Place on waxed paper lined baking sheet.
Chill.
Makes about 100.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add fruits and their juices and pecans.
Congeal mixture in 9 x 12-inch glass cake pan. Whip cream cheese and sour cream with sugar; spread smoothly over congealed salad.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese. Mix in the dry mix and the breast of chicken. Shape into a ball and roll in finely chopped pecans. Chill and serve with assorted crackers.

title: chopped chicken liver
directions: Saute onions for 5 minutes. Remove from oleo. Add livers and saute for 10 minutes. Grind livers, onions and eggs in food grinder or chop fine by hand.
Add seasoning.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce or on crackers.
Good at parties!

title: broccoli beef
directions: Marinate beef with soy sauce, sesame oil and cooking wine. Heat peanut oil in preheated wok.
Quickly stir-fry beef until meat changes color.
Pull beef up on the side of the wok to stop it from cooking.
Add water to wok and place broccoli along sides of wok and steam with the lid on the wok for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove excess water from the wok.
Pull all the food down into the center of the wok and stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together butter, 2 cups flour and confectioners sugar. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and cut broccoli into florets.
Clean and cut green pepper into pieces.
Cut cheese into bite-size pieces (I use Longhorn cheese).
Add grated carrot.
Cut hard-boiled eggs into pieces.
Add bacon.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat in microwave 3 to 4 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer crushed Doritos on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour chicken broth over this.
Layer cubed chicken, onion, pepper and 1/2 cup cheese.
Blend soups with chili powder and pour over cheese.
Chop Ro-Tel tomatoes and pour over soups.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: avocado dip
directions: Put all in blender and mix well. Pour on platter and cool. Top with onion, peppers, tomatoes and cheese. Serve
with tortilla chips.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Oil and flour 9 X 12 inch pan; bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: soft raisin cookie
directions: Boil raisins in water until water is almost gone.
Cool. Cream together shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add to raisins.
Sift flour and soda together and add to cookie dough. Drop onto cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheets to 375°.
Boil sweet potatoes in water until easily pierced by fork.
Cool slightly.
Place cooked and peeled potatoes in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in spices, salt and evaporated milk. Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake on preheated cookie sheets near center of oven for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack, garnish with marshmallows, if desired.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in margarine in a skillet.
Add a Tbsp. flour and stir to thicken.
Add chicken broth, milk, mushroom soup, pimentos, olives and margarine. Cook spaghetti.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine and shape ingredients into a loaf.
Place the loaf in a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots into strips.
Mix garlic and minced onions in oil. Saute carrots in mixture for 5 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper, mustard and vinegar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove pickling spices and put carrots and juice in shallow dish.
Cover with thinly sliced onions.
Baste carrots for added flavor while they chill.
For pickle flavor, don't tie spices in cheesecloth.
You can leave spice bag in carrots until cool and squeeze to get full flavor.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to instructions on box.
Combine cooked macaroni with next 5 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and top with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: adobo
directions: Marinate meat for at least 1 hour.
Boil all together.
Don't mix while boiling; it will become too sour.
When meat is cooked and tender, take out meat and fry meat until brown.
Pour liquid over fried meat and serve warm.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: In medium bowl, lightly mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, 1/2 can Hunt's tomato sauce, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining Hunt's sauce with rest of ingredients; pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste loaf several times.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chips and white chocolate in large saucepan on low heat. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Decorate as desired.
Refrigerate until firm. Store at room temperature.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, cream cheese and margarine until well blended. Add everything else except pecans.
Refrigerate until chilled. Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: foolproof apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add vanilla, butter flavoring, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt to cream mixture.
Sift soda and flour and add to mixture until smooth, then add apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake in tube pan that has been greased.
Bake at 325° for about 60 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: veal and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper tenderloin slices.
Roll in flour.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour milk over the top.
Cover and bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Makes its own gravy.

title: herbed green beans
directions: Break beans and place in 1 1/2 quart dish, add water.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave at High for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 3 or 4 minutes.
Place pepper, oil and onion in 1 quart dish. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Drain beans, add pepper mixture and remaining ingredients, stir well.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 round 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Combine first 6 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add next 3 ingredients and beat well.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 40 minutes in round pans.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out of pans.
Cool and frost.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put first 6 ingredients into skillet.
Cover and cook 1 minute. Uncover and cook, turning with spatula, until barely tender (about 5 minutes).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Toss.
Put in serving bowl.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Crumble 1 package Ritz crackers over casserole.
Pour margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Can easily be doubled.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Set in refrigerator for 1 hour to cool, then pour over strawberries in cooked and cooled pie crust.
Chill until set.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Place shrimp and onions in layers in a sealable container. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over shrimp.
seal. Refrigerate for 6 or more hours.
Shake occasionally.
This will keep for over a week.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning. Mix; spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick.
Mix until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with mixer.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until center is set, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes, lettuce and cheese, if desired.

title: egg crouton casserole
directions: Grease 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Place croutons on bottom, then add cheese, reserving a little, followed by crumbled bacon.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard, pepper and onion powder.
Pour over crouton mixture.
Top with reserved cheese. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 60 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham chowder
directions: In stock pot, cook carrots, celery, onion and potatoes in 5 cups water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add ham, butter, salt and pepper.
Blend flour into milk; stir into soup.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils; turn heat to low and allow to simmer, partially covered, 10 to 20 minutes to develop flavor.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine in pan, peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme; set aside. Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Boil and stir constantly for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add to Marshmallow Creme mixture.
Beat until thick.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Fudge will set slowly.

title: baked apple(serves 1)
directions: Core apple; sprinkle with cinnamon and wrap in foil.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Baste chicken in sauce while broiling.
Cook about 1 hour. Makes enough sauce for 2 chickens.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add nuts and apples.
Stir in flour one cup at a time.
Mix well.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
You can add 1 pound of candied fruit.
Makes a delicious and easy fruitcake.

title: bacon monkey bread
directions: Combine bacon, Parmesan cheese and onion.
Set aside.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip each piece in margarine and layer 1/3 in a lightly greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle half of the bacon mixture over the biscuits.
Repeat, ending with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Melt butter and dissolve sugar; add curry powder.
Pour
butter and sugar mixture over fruit and bake at 325° until bubbly.
Delicious with any kind of meat.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans and drain.
Put beans and water in a pot and bring to a boil.
Continue to boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand one hour.
Add onion, salt, ham and carrots to the beans.
Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours or until beans are soft.
For thicker soup, simmer longer.
Add additional water for thinner soup.
This soup freezes very well and tastes just as good.

title: marimore cake(yields one 8-inch double layer cake or one 9 x 13-inch cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; mix well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour mixture.

Add cooled melted chocolate and vanilla. Fold in egg whites and chopped nuts. Pour into 2 greased 8-inch cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: apple cider bread or muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or eighteen muffin cups.
Cream the butter and 1 1/4 cups of the sugar together in a large bowl.
Add eggs and cream thoroughly.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Add them to the egg mixture, alternating with the cider.
Stir in chopped apples.
Divide the batter between the prepared loaf pans.
Combine the remaining 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon in a small bowl and sprinkle it over the batter.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 70 minutes for bread or for 30 to 40 minutes for muffins or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Yields 2 loaves or 18 muffins.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Mix broth, pepper, carrot and celery in saucepan. Heat to a boil. Stir in noodles and chicken. Cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until noodles are done.

title: ladyfinger dessert
directions: Line a loaf pan, sides and bottom with split ladyfingers.
Mix pudding mix, Dream Whip and milk.
Beat 5 minutes until fluffy. Pour into pan and chill or freeze.
Before serving, remove from pan and garnish with whipped cream, chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: chicken strata
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mushroom soup, eggs and milk. Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Spread mushroom soup over the top before baking.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over casserole.
Sprinkle more cheese on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in a saucepan.
Add boiling water and cook, stirring until clear and thick.
Let stand until cold.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff, but not dry.
Beat at low speed.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat in cold cornstarch mixture.
Beat on high until well beaten.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes after putting on pie.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll into small balls, not more than 1-inch wide.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not allow to brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: beefy ball
directions: Be sure beef, pecans and onion are all chopped fine.
Mix well and make into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle paprika on the next day (optional).
Spread on crackers to serve.

title: bacon rolls
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sprinkle sugars and cinnamon on top of batter after mixing the ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour in bread loaf pan lined with wax paper.
This recipe doubled makes 3 loaves.

title: festive tossed salad
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, onion and salt. Cover and process until blended. With blender running, gradually add oil. Add poppy seeds and blend.

title: microwave enchilada roll-ups
directions: On an enchilada, spread a layer of mayonnaise and place a couple of slices of roast beef or turkey.
Add small amount of lettuce and place in microwave for about 1 minute.
Remove and place 1 tablespoon of picante sauce over enchilada.
Tomato may be added, if desired.

title: lo-cal lasagna
directions: Spray a pan with Pam.
Brown turkey with onion, green pepper, salt and oregano.
Remove from heat and add spaghetti sauce and pizza sauce.
Put 1 to 2 teaspoons of this in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add uncooked lasagna noodles.
Layer with turkey mix, Ricotta cheese and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese and bake, covered with foil, for 45 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar together into a large bowl. Add buttermilk, beaten egg and melted margarine.
Stir in raisins. Knead well and put in greased 8 x 8 x 3-inch pan. Cut cross on top and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: gum drop fudge
directions: Line a 9 inch square pan with foil.
In sauce pan heat the candy coating, milk and salt over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and gum drops.
Spread into lined 9 inch square pan.
Cover and put in refrigerater until firm.
Using foil, remove from pan and cut into 1 inch squares.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: layered party plate
directions: Soften cream cheese and mash on serving plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle shrimp over sauce and top with grated cheese.
Mix onions, bell pepper and tomatoes; sprinkle over cheese layer.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hersheys in microwave or saucepan.
Add Cool Whip to melted mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Quickly pour into pie crust and cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add broccoli and cook until tender. Add soup, cheese (cut up), Accent, mushrooms and almonds.
Put in large casserole dish and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.

title: charleston red rice
directions: Cook rice in 6 cups salted water until light and fluffy, not soft and sticky.
Fry bacon until brown and crisp.
Saute onions in 4 tablespoons of bacon fat until clear.
Add tomato sauce and paste, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Place the cooked rice in a buttered baking dish and stir all seasonings in rice.
Place in oven and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Crumble bacon over top.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: tomatoless chili
directions: Chop garlic and onions.
Saute in small amount of butter.
Add 1 tablespoon chili powder and stir to mix.
If needed, add 1 more tablespoon chili powder.
Brown hamburger and add 1 tablespoon chili powder and a dash of salt.
Add 1/4 cup flour to hamburger and stir in.
Add beans, water, pepper and more chili powder to taste.
Turn flame down low and cook 4 or 5 hours.
Serve with crackers or buttered bread.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.
Mix together flour, cheese, salt and pepper. Roll potatoes in mixture.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes in pan and bake 1 hour at 375°. Turn potatoes after 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: triple chocolate fudge
directions: Line an 8 inch sq. pan with waxed paper or foil.
Set aside. Melt chocolate in a saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat, cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until creamy.
Add confectioners sugar beating continually until smooth.
Beat melted chocolate into the cream cheese mixture.
Add pecans and mix well with a wooden spoon. Pour fudge into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
Cut into 1 inch squares.

title: applesauce cake squares
directions: Place unsweetened chocolate and butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; stir until chocolate melts.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, applesauce, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl; mix well. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to applesauce mixture, stirring well.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Spoon the batter into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with Nutty Coconut Frosting; cut into squares.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: pistachio-coconut surprise salad
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add coconut and pineapple; stir until blended.
Spoon into an 8 x 4 or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze until firm.
Or instead of freezing, fruit salad can be served immediately or chilled.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie shell.
Beat all together very thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tahitian punch
directions: In large punch bowl, stir together juices, and add lemon-lime drink.
Using
an ice cream scoop or spoon, float sherbet on top. Serve immediately.

title: cold pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese out on to the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour chili sauce over cream cheese and spread out.
Sprinkle the rest of the ingredients (except the cheese) over it.
Last, sprinkle the cheese on top.
Eat with Fritos.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan; cook at medium heat.
Keep stirring until dough comes off side of pan.
Take out of pan and let cool for a few minutes; knead for 5 minutes.

title: choc shake
directions: Blend all ingredients together until desired consistency. Makes a great low-fat shake.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine or butter.
Layer in the following order on top: graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and condensed milk.
Pour on top; don't mix.
Just put one on top of each other.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool a very few minutes and cut in squares as you wish.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs, vanilla and saccharin.
Add other ingredients.
Fold in dates, applesauce and nuts.
Bake at 340° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in half; slice one half in slices.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with soft ice cream.
Chunk other half of angel food cake, put on top of ice cream.
Freeze.
Serve with strawberries.

title: hot and spicy sauteed mushrooms
directions: In a
large
skillet melt 1/2 cup butter to saute mushrooms. Once
tender,
place to the side.
Use same skillet to melt second
cup
butter.
Add peppers, green onions and garlic. Cook
over	medium	heat until crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer
2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly
heated. Stir
once	halfway through cooking.
You can use canned mushrooms.

title: p-nut butter pie
directions: Mix together with mixer and pour into graham cracker crust. Freeze for 1 hour before serving.
Keep remainder in refrigerator after serving.
The ready baked chocolate crust is great with this also.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine with salad dressing.

title: beef and biscuits casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion
and
pepper in large skillet. Drain grease.
Stir in
tomato
sauce, chili powder and garlic salt. Simmer while
preparing
dough.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Layer over
the	bottom	of
ungreased 8 to 9-inch square baking pan.	Combine
cup
cheese
(reserve remaining cheese for topping),
sour	cream and egg; mix well. Remove meat mixture from heat
and stir in sour cream mixture; spoon over dough.
Arrange
remaining	biscuit
layers on top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake
at
for
25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: crab dip mold
directions: Mix Knox, water and mushroom soup together and heat to boil; cool.
Mix cream cheese, onions, celery, mayo and crab meat together.
Combine with Knox mixture.
Place in 5 to 6-cup mold and chill 5 to 8 hours.
Remove from mold to serve.

title: christine's cheesecake
directions: Combine cake mix, oleo, and 1 egg and mix well.
Put into 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan, patting dough with hands to cover bottom of pan completely.
Beat together all remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture over cake crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.
It tastes better if made 24 hours before serving.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix crushed wafers, sugar, nuts and cocoa together well.
Work up with hands and gradually add rum.
Make into small balls and roll each one in powdered sugar.
Store in tin box for a few days before using.
This makes about 36 balls.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Tastes best made day before serving and reheated.

title: jack's cocoa cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.

Mix flour, sugar and salt. Set aside. Bring to a boil the water, oleo, oil and cocoa. Pour over flour mixture. Add vanilla. Stir in eggs (do not beat). Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients; let marinate overnight.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, vanilla pudding, eggs, water and Crisco oil at cake speed for 5 minutes.
Fold in 1 cup of semi-sweet chocolate chips and grated chocolate.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and 1/4 cup grated German chocolate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Put points together.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with hash brown potatoes and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients and pour into and uncooked 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° until filling is firm.

title: bran rolls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and cool to lukewarm. Mix the yeast in the lukewarm water, egg and flour. Combine the two mixtures; cover and let rise 2 hours. Pinch off about 32 rolls. Add enough flour to handle. Place in 2 well-greased pie plates. Let rise again. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: When adding the Miracle Whip, be sure to spread a good smooth thick layer.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 4 hours or more.
Don't toss it, the salad stays crispier longer.

title: hot punch
directions: Let ingredients come to a boil.
Simmer for 4 to 5 minutes. Add 2 cups orange juice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt cheese together with all ingredients on top of stove. Pour over unbaked pie crust and top with another unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Pop a large bowl of popcorn and set aside. Mix butter, sugar and syrup. Put burner on medium heat, and when mixture starts to melt and it begins to boil, time for 6 minutes. When time is up, add baking soda. Stir until mixture turns smooth. If adding peanuts, mix them with the popcorn before pouring mixture over the popcorn. Mix well.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine softened butter or margarine with garlic.
Cook broccoli until tender, drain well.
Season with salt and pepper. Mash with a fork.
Slice bread lengthwise and hollow out both halves.
In bottom half, spread with garlic butter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then alternate layer of mashed broccoli, Parmesan and Mozzarella.
Spread garlic butter on top layer of bread.
Put halves together and wrap tightly in foil.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Slice and serve hot or warm.

title: chicago cocktail
directions: Stir brandy and bitters with ice.
Strain into champagne glasses.
Fill with iced champagne.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Add ingredients in order and mix.
Add boiling water very slowly, stirring, until mixture reaches a doughlike consistency. Let cool and knead until smooth.
It will stay good for a long time.
Store in an airtight container.
Smells great.

title: taco baskets
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning, beans and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In large deep fryer, have oil hot and drop in tortilla shell.
Hold clean emptied one pound coffee can in middle of shell.
Tortilla will curl up around can and turn light brown when done.
Drain on paper towel and set aside.
Fry remaining shells and drain.
Prepare cheese sauce by blending cheese mix and milk; stir over medium heat for 7 minutes or until thick.
Fill each fried shell half full of lettuce.
Cover with meat.
Pour cheese sauce over meat and garnish with green onions.

title: pepper steak
directions: In skillet, put in 1 tablespoon hot oil.
Cook beef, half at a time, until brown, stirring often.
Remove; set aside.
Put in remaining 1 tablespoon of oil.
Cook peppers and onion with garlic powder until tender, stirring often.
Stir in gravy and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Return beef to skillet. Serve over rice.

title: apricot-pineapple delight
directions: Drain fruits separately; reserve juices. Chop apricots. Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water; add 1/2 cup pineapple juice and 1/2 cup apricot juice. Chill until thickened.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and apricots.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch container. Chill until firm.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor thoroughly.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes, then cool.
Add orange juice, lemonade and gin.
Freeze mixture.
When ready to serve, fill glass half full of mixture and half with 7-Up or Sprite.
Great to keep on hand in the freezer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, syrup, butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set in middle.

title: copper pennies
directions: Place carrots, onions and peppers in layers in a bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots. Refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: shower punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Freeze some the night before in an ice ring.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain and cool. Peel and cube potatoes.
Combine potato, celery, sweet pickles, eggs and onions and toss gently.
In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Spoon mayonnaise mixture over potato mixture and toss gently.
May be served warm or cold.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Blend in vanilla and gradually add flour.
Add pecans.
Chill several hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.
Cool on rack.

title: onion dip
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon on both sides until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Save half of 1 slice for garnish.
Crumble remaining bacon.
In medium bowl, blend soup mix, bacon, sour cream, horseradish and mustard.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve with chips or cut up raw vegetables.
Garnish top with bacon.

title: cheezy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix ground beef, onions, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, egg, green peppers, cheese, and tomato sauce.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13 pan.
Form to shape of pan.
Mix tomato paste and sugar in a small bowl and pour over top of meat mixture.
Cook for a hour or until firm.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix together and bake in small shallow bowl or pie plate at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with a mild cracker.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ground cloves.
Beat butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Combine buttermilk and apple butter.
Add alternately with the flour mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly on cake rack.
Frost cooled cake with creamy vanilla frosting.

title: taco salad
directions: Follow directions on back of taco seasoning in preparing ground beef. Dice tomatoes in large bowl; chop lettuce and place on top of tomatoes.
Add can of kidney beans to beef mixture and pour over lettuce.
Pour crushed Doritos over beef.
Add Thousand Island dressing over Doritos.
Put cheese over all just before serving.

title: cinnamon potpourri ornaments
directions: Select an apple that is ripe, but firm and well shaped.
Peel smooth, then ream out stem and blossom ends.
You're now ready for carving.
Use a very sharp knife.
Dip the apple in lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Start carving by cutting brow line.
Then cut two vertical lines at right angles for the nose.
Cut in and around nose and out over cheek.
Hollow out slits for eyes, about 1/2-inch below brow line and in toward nose bridge.
Remove enough below nose to form chin and mouth.
Carve mouth by cutting very thin slits, which will dry into perfect shape.

title: honey mustard, ham and potato salad
directions: Cut
ham
into bite size strips.
Set aside.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Cook potatoes in boiling water in a large skillet until tender, about 10 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed. Add melted butter; mix well. Pour 1/2 batter in 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels and milk in double boiler or microwave. Spoon over cake. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over caramel. Pour remaining batter over mixture and bake approximately 15 minutes or until cake is done.

title: egg-rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Chill. Makes 6 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; add sauce.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix noodles with sour cream, cream cheese and green onions.
In casserole dish, put layer of meat sauce, noodles and then grated cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: kool-aid pies
directions: Chill Pet milk until it's icy, then whip.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Put in icebox.
Serve in 1 hour.
Will make 2 small pies.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can be topped with cracker crumbs or bread crumbs.

title: apple pie
directions: Cut up apples into small pieces and place into bottom crust. (Use frozen pie crust or make own from basic pie crust recipe.) Mix the remaining ingredients, except condensed milk and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Pour over apples.
For top of crust, mix the condensed milk and 1 tablespoon of sugar together.
Brush on sides of bottom crust, then place top crust on and brush mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or plain.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Turn crock-pot to high heat and cook 2 hours.
Lower heat to low and cook until all ingredients are fork-tender.
Serves 6.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Cook bacon until almost done.
Dice shrimp to very small pieces (run through a coarse grinder if you'd prefer).
Dice water chestnuts in same manner.
Combine shrimp, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Season to taste.
Split Kaiser rolls and scrape out soft centers of both halves.
Spoon shrimp mixture into hollows of Kaiser rolls.
Top with slices of tomatoes and bacon.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and toss with herb seasoned dressing mix.
Take 1/2 of this mixture and mix with squash, soup, sour cream and onion.
Pour into greased baking dish and spread.
Put rest of dressing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: islander's delight
directions: Cook apple, pepper and curry in butter until pepper is tender. Add soup and water.
Heat.
Stir now and then.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: pink delite
directions: Fold together; chill for 2 hours.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in 1 cup boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once; stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Next add eggs, one at a time, making sure you beat smooth after you add each egg.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Drain noodles.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Combine noodles, sauce and ham.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crumble wafers; then mix all ingredients together.
Press into pan.
If you have a Jell-O mold, press into it.
Then chill. Serve.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peanuts, in top of a double boiler.
Add peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° glass pan).
Melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl beat cheese until fluffy.
Mix Eagle Brand, vanilla and egg.
Pour into prepared pan and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick into center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature and chill before cutting.
Keep refrigerated!!!

title: crispy raisin drops
directions: Cream the butter and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and soda. Gradually blend into creamed mixture. Stir in granola and raisins. Drop by heaping teaspoonful on greased or nonstick baking sheets.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes on baking sheets before removing to wire racks to complete cooling.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Dip fresh cauliflower, broccoli, celery, cubed radishes, onions or green peppers.
Blend all the ingredients well before you do so.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Dissolve sugar in evaporated milk. Add vanilla flavoring, salt and bananas. Stir in sweet milk to fill line of ice cream churn. Freeze in ice cream churn as directed.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove bones and dice.
Melt oleo and stir in flour.
Add sour cream; cook and stir until bubbly.
Add soup, chicken and chili.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove and sprinkle with cheese, then bake 10 minutes longer. Serve over rice or crepes.

title: one cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into walnut size balls and flatten on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each cookie with 1 tsp. red or white sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 - 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: lamb curry and rice
directions: Cut lamb legs in strips.
Add black pepper and salt to 3 tablespoons flour; mix good with flour.
Pour 1 cup oil into skillet or frying pan.
When oil is hot, add lamb.
Keep turning until meat is soft; then add rest of flour.
Keep turning until gravy thickens.
Add water; stir.
Move to larger pot, if needed. Cook.
Lower heat for 20 minutes of until meat is soft and gravy is right.
Fry bacon until crisp; chop up.
Cook 1 1/2 cups rice.
Put in separate bowls chopped pepper, celery, eggs, peanuts, coconut, raisins, orange peel, bacon and curry powder.
Put spoon of rice on plate and all of each kind of chopping over rice.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Saute onions in butter in large skillet until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat.

title: quick soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large pot. Add onion and cook 5 to 10 minutes. Drain grease off meat. Stir in the flour to thicken. Add all other ingredients. Cook about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or cornbread. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Cream together shortening and oleo.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Whip with mixer until well blended and fluffy.
Serve with apple slices.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Partially cook noodles and set aside.
Mix soup and milk; add peas, meat and noodles.
Layer in greased casserole half of mixture, then layer of cheese.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grits casserole
directions: Pour the grits into boiling water to which salt has been added.
Mix well, and cook until thickened.
Add the butter, beaten eggs, milk and cheese.
Stir thoroughly and place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: whiskey sauce
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter.
Add 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Cream together and then blend in beaten egg.
Pour into double boiler or use saucepan and heat slowly.
Beat well with a wire whisk.
When heated, but not boiling, remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons of good whiskey.
Serve over steamed pudding, warm apple pudding or baked apple.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and put in bread pan.
Use lid or aluminum foil.

title: pound cake favorite
directions: Cream the butter. Add 2 cups sugars (sift sugars together). Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat until well blended.
Mix in flavoring.
Add flour that has been mixed with baking powder. Alternate mixing flour and milk.
Add egg whites that have been beaten to stiff stage; fold into batter.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 1/2-inch loaf pans or 3 (6-inch) loaf pans.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add eggs, oil and strawberries.
Mix by hand. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325` for one hour.

title: fettuccine with fresh tomato and basil sauce(serves 6 - 358 calories per each serving)
directions: Combine tomatoes, garlic, oil and salt and pepper to taste in a large bowl.
Stir to mix well.
Serve over hot, freshly cooked fettuccine in a warmed serving bowl.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Remove cover the last 3 hours.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes enough for 12 picnic servings.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and chill dough about 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, sugar and salt; with fingers, rub in butter.
Add raisins, then buttermilk until moistened.
On floured board, knead dough for 1 minute.
Add little more flour to dough if sticky.
Shape dough into ball and put in buttered dish.
With sharp knife, cut an X on top of loaf and brush with milk.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool completely before slicing.

title: chicken au miel
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in paper bag.
Add the chicken and shake.
Put chicken pieces, skin side down, in shallow casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup melted margarine over.
Sprinkle with remaining flour.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Blend the honey, lemon juice, tarragon and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Turn chicken over; cover with mixture.
Return to oven for another 30 minutes or longer, basting twice.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and drained fruit.
Let stand until marshmallows have softened.
Combine mayonnaise, whipped cream and cheese.
Mix well until creamy.
Add fruit.
Pour into refrigerator tray and freeze 3 hours.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 8 large servings.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Mix and cook in double boiler until thick.
May be a little thin until cool.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread, and refrigerate overnight.
Cut out middle of bread.
Slice up sections removed and put around outside edge of tray.
Put dip in middle of bread.

title: bourbon slushies
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Freeze in container you can scoop the semi-frozen slushies from.
Put a couple of scoops in a glass and pour 7-Up or ginger ale over and stir.
Should look like or have the consistency of a frozen Margarita.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream, Miracle Whip, onion and drained, squeezed dry spinach.
Blend in the soup mix.
Put into an airtight container and refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.
It spreads well onto crackers or rye toast.
It will keep for 3 days before it becomes watery.

title: no bake lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, lemonade and topping together well.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill well before serving.
This pie freezes well.

title: freezer dumplings
directions: Mix; let stand in refrigerator 2 hours.
Roll thin; cut and put on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
When frozen, put in freezer bags.

title: quick and easy pizza sandwiches
directions: Mix ground chuck, salt, chili sauce and oregano together lightly.
Split English muffins in half.
On each half, spread meat mixture about 1/2-inch thick.
Place several slices of onion on top of meat.
Cut pieces of cheese in half and crisscross them on top of meat and onion mixture.
Place in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbling.
Serve immediately.

title: squash and hominy dish
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In large skillet, combine the zucchini or squash, onion, butter and water; cook slowly until tender. Add the hominy, pepper, sour cream, salt and 1 cup cheese. Pour into a greased 3-quart baking dish. Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with crushed corn chips. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Sift all dry ingredients in a medium bowl.
Add oil and eggs; mix well.
Add milk and sweet potato; mix well, then add nuts last.
Bake in pound cake pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: hamburger sour cream casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown meat and drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and flour.
Simmer until thickened.
Combine sour cream and salt. Place cooked noodles in bottom of quart casserole.
Layer with the sour cream mixture and top with the hamburger mixture.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie or egg pie without coconut
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Blend; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake 25 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: eggless pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, spices, soda and salt.
In a bowl mix oil, sugar and pumpkin by hand.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin a little at a time, until blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done, 45 to 50 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put chicken in buttered dish, 8 x 8-inch or 13 x 9-inch, depending on number of chicken breasts.
Pour undiluted soup over chicken breasts.
Place 1 slice cheese on each piece of chicken. Spread prepared dressing over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and cook slowly.
Add cocoa and stir.
Beat egg yolks and stir them into hot mixture. Add butter and vanilla.
Continue stirring and cook until stiff. Cool and put in cool pie shell.
Add meringue and bake until light brown.
Cool.

title: recipe for child raising
directions: Trust in the Lord with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs. Add milk, sugar, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and nutmeg; beat again.
Add bread and raisins, then stir.
Pour into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake until light brown on top. Serves 8.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients, as desired.
Mix well and drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over pecans and coconut. Combine cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar; pour over cake batter, leaving 1/2 to 1-inch on sides.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Serve from pan.

title: loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs (separated); add other ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for around an hour.

title: light and crispy pecan chicken(makes eight 3-ounce servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Combine flour, cayenne and salt. Combine egg whites and water.
Combine bread crumbs and pecans. Dip chicken pieces in seasoned flour, then egg whites, then bread crumbs mixture.
Brush sheet pan with oil.
Place chicken on pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake additional 5 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cow in the garden
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Place a layer of beef mixture, a layer of corn and a layer of tomatoes in casserole; repeat, ending with tomatoes.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Top with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Finish filling with water up to a gallon.
May freeze and serve slushy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water until thick.
Before removing from heat, add jello and marshmallows.
Allow to dissolve.
Stir in celery, apples and nuts.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows melt.
Remove and cool.
Add liqueurs.
Whip cream until it peaks.
Fold into marshmallow mixture and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate cream drops
directions: Cream the margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Add cooled chocolate and dry ingredients.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chili mac
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water with 1 tablespoon cooking oil. Drain off liquid.
Meanwhile, brown beef and onion.
Add tomato juice, brown sugar, salt, pepper, chili powder and cooked macaroni.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into dish and serve. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: 30-minute spanish chicken
directions: Heat water for the noodles and let come to a boil in a separate pot.

Add noodles to boiling water when you add the mushrooms and black olives to the Spanish chicken mixture in the large skillet. Begin by sauteed chicken strips in a large/deep skillet on medium-low heat with the olive oil, turning occasionally.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add shortening and cut in with pastry blender.
Add yeast to buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture slowly, stirring in with a fork. Turn dough out onto lightly floured board; knead several times. Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450°
for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 2 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Spoon out and make a ball with dough.
Put on cookie sheet and press down with a glass to make it round.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: burgundy stew
directions: Mix meat and vegetables in Dutch oven.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir in tomatoes and wine.
Cook in oven for 4 hours at 325° covered.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: orange-date-nut cake
directions: Dredge chopped nuts and dates in 1/2 cup of the flour.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add nuts, dates and orange rind.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese sauce(for potatoes, broccoli or cauliflower)
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour and stir into a dry paste. Add milk slowly, about 1/4 cup at a time.
Stir often.
After all milk is added and a thickening is formed, add chunks of cheese. Pour melted sauce over any vegetable.

title: stromboli
directions: Press bread out on greased cookie sheet.
In center of dough, layer the rest of the ingredients.
Fold end to end and pinch together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's biscuit pudding
directions: Soak biscuits in enough milk to soften biscuits.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, 3 eggs and vanilla; mix well.
If you like, you may now add raisins, coconut or pineapple for a different taste.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: stuffed baked sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rinse and dry sweet potatoes well.
Place potatoes on baking sheet; bake for 55 to 60 minutes, or until tender.
Do not turn off oven.
Cool potatoes until easy to handle.
When potatoes are cool, cut in half lengthwise.
With spoon, scoop out pulp from 8 potato halves into large bowl and discard skins.
Scoop out pulp from remaining 8 potato halves, leaving 1/4 inch potato intact on skin to make shells.
Place pulp in same large bowl; return potato shells to same baking sheet.

title: "hello dollies"(a perfect treat for any occasion)
directions: Melt stick of butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with graham cracker crumbs, 1 layer of chopped walnuts, 1 layer of semi-sweet chocolate bits and 1 layer of coconut.
Cover with condensed milk.

title: spinbeefchee
directions: Squeeze liquid out of spinach.
Brown beef and onion in large skillet.
Add garlic salt, pepper and salt.
Stir in mushrooms. Cook over low heat 5 minutes; drain off all liquid.
In large bowl, combine tomato sauce, sour cream, basil, oregano, cottage cheese and eggs.
Stir in bacon, spinach and meat mixture.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan and 2/3 cup of Cheddar cheese; mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jellies
directions: Combine gelatin and cold water; stir and let stand at least 5 minutes until thick.

title: low-fat chicken and noodles
directions: Skin chicken breasts or legs.
Boil until cooked.
Chop in cubes.
In chicken broth, cook celery and broccoli, just a few minutes.
You still want it to be crispy.
Cook noodles.
Drain. Put all in 3-quart casserole dish.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Add the brown sugar.
Mix and add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Will be thick.
Spread in cookie sheet pan.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips on top of mixture.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown beef in a large pot.
Drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti.
Cover and cook on medium heat until tender (about 20 to 30 minutes), stirring occasionally.
In a bowl, mix Ricotta, eggs, parsley, salt, oregano and garlic powder.
Scoop half of spaghetti into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with Ricotta cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Put rest of spaghetti mix on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
After baking, let stand for 5 minutes.

title: milly's meat loaf
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients and shape into loaf pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes, basting often.
Serve with the sauce.

title: walnut cream sauce(this recipe is for those times when you throw your diet out!)
directions: Saute onions, tomatoes, nuts, basil and garlic in olive oil for 2 minutes.
Add cream and simmer until thickened.
Serve over cooked fettucini immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lush mush
directions: Mix well and freeze.
When serving, fill glass one-half to three-fourths full and the rest with 7-Up.
Will last a long time frozen.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans with string bean juice.
Drain wax beans.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add oil, pepper and salt and stir well.
Add the drained beans, green pepper and onions.
Stir well, but gently, in order to keep beans whole.
Place in large, covered dish and let set in refrigerator overnight, mixing and stirring occasionally.
Serve until thoroughly chilled.

title: orange macadamia nut cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, powdered sugar, and cornstarch.
Using a pastry blender, cut in butter till mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with cream, whipped topping or ice cream.

title: diabetic holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve in a chilled punch bowl.

title: fruity cottage cheese salad
directions: In an airtight container, stir together cottage cheese, apple, dried fruit bits, mayonnaise and cinnamon. Chill overnight.

title: english pea salad
directions: Heat English peas until hot; drain liquid.
Add chopped onions and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: ginny's light melody
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large baking dish, add sausage and milk.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Add shredded cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Parboil cabbage, onion, potatoes, carrots, celery and bell pepper for about 20 minutes.
Add parboiled vegetables to the sausage mixture.
Add some vegetable broth if you have room in baking dish.
Add English peas or kidney beans.
Bake for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Cut light cheese slices in half and place on top of casserole for the last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and soup on low heat.
Then mix shrimp, onion, celery and mayonnaise with cream cheese and soup.
Chill for several hours.
Good with chips or party crackers.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water together.
When almost jelled, add pineapple, marshmallows and banana.
Let set until jelled. Cook sugar, flour, egg, pineapple juice and margarine, stirring constantly until thick.
Cook over low heat.
Let cool and stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over top of Jell-O and sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: huck finn oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix margarine, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in rest of ingredients until blended.

title: church cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Drop on a cookie sheet and flatten a little. Sprinkle sugar on top. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mama's chocolate fudge
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until medium-hard ball stage.
Take off and beat.
Add pecans, if desired.
Beat until begins to thicken.
Pour up quickly.
Cut before it sets too long.

title: hawaiian crunch appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cereal, peanuts, raisins and banana chips in ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Heat margarine and honey in 1-quart saucepan over low heat until margarine is melted.
Stir in cinnamon and salt.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Toss until evenly coated.
Bake for 10 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in popcorn and coconut.
Sprinkle with additional salt, if desired.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken rice dinner
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken pieces.
In a large skillet over medium heat, brown the chicken in oil.
Place rice in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion and garlic; top with mushrooms.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water; pour over all.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken juices run clear and rice is tender.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Yields 5 servings.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Mix well until well blended. Beat 4 egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Place in well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan and bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scatter cheese in pastry shell.
In a bowl, beat eggs with half and half, then pour onto cheese. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Have beef and pork ground together.
Slowly saute meat, onions, garlic and other seasonings until meat is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix spaghetti, butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese together. Arrange in bottom of an ovenproof pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cook ground beef and onions; stir in can of tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano and garlic salt.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
In small bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with seasoned flour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Melt 1 stick oleo; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together the Ritz crackers, pecans and 1/2 cup sugar in plastic bag.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add pinch of cream of tartar, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Mix.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Pat artichokes dry and cut in half.
Blend artichokes with eggs, pepperoni, Mozzarella, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick, when inserted, comes out clean.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and dry chicken.
Place chicken, skin side up, in baking dish.
Salt and pepper; dot with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: adeline's spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Put in a 10 x 13-inch pan and add onion, green pepper and margarine.
Break up (uncooked) spaghetti into meat mixture.
Pour tomato juice and paste on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Stir 3 times while cooking.
May add cheese on top and bake a little longer.
May double ingredients. Delicious even the next day.

title: tuna broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Arrange broccoli in the bottom of a dish.
Put tuna over broccoli.
Pour soup over tuna.
Crush chips and put them on the top.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Sometimes I put slices of American cheese on top of the soup before I put the chips on.
It gives it a different taste.

title: goat cheese quesadilla
directions: Prepare the Pico De Gallo and set aside.
Prepare the Guacamole; cover tightly with plastic wrap and set aside.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place frozen meatballs in a single layer in a baking pan for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
In a medium saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, tomato sauce, and 6 Tbsp. orange marmalade.
Bring to a low boil and reduce to a simmer for 5 minutes.
Cover meatballs in sauce and keep warm. Makes approximately 5 cups sauce.

title: deer hunter's pie
directions: Saute the hamburger in a skillet until it is lightly browned and completely separated.
Arrange a layer of potatoes over the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Follow with a layer of meat, a layer of onions and a layer of apples.
Repeat until you have used up all of the ingredients.
Heat the beef stock, add the nutmeg, pepper and salt.
Stir well so that all of the salt is dissolved.
Pour this over the casserole.
Sprinkle the bread crumbs over the top and add little dabs of butter if you like. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: flower pot dirt cake
directions: Mix and set aside pudding and milk.
Mix together butter and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend into pudding mixture.
In food processor, crush Oreos until crumbly like dirt.
Layer cookies and pudding mix in flower pot ending with cookies.
(You may want to line pot with foil.) Decorate with gummy worms and silk flowers.
Have fun watching people's reactions.

title: golden delicious torte
directions: In a bowl, blend butter with 1/4 cup sugar.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt and blend.
To the butter mixture, add walnuts, egg yolks, lemon rind and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for 1 hour.

title: breakfast parfait
directions: Divide yogurt between 2 (8 ounce) glasses and layer other ingredients with yogurt.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serves 2.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa; add milk.
Cook until thick.

title: spanish lemon pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks.
Add to yolks-the milk and the lemon juice with rind.
Beat whites till stiff.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.

title: cinnamon rolls(serves 15)
directions: Barely bring milk, shortening and sugar to a boil.
Chill. Mix yeast with lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make cake-like batter.
Let rise 2 hours.
Add salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour to make a soft dough, still sticky, but not much. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out.
Add butter, sugar and cinnamon. Roll out and slice 1 1/2 to 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bristol inn cheese roll
directions: Grate or break up Cheddar.
Mix with cream cheese and garlic. Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out by hand into uniform 1 inch thick. Roll thoroughly in chili powder.
Can be made a day or two ahead. Excellent for holiday serving.

title: grandma garrett's cole slaw
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour over cabbage and carrots.
Add mixture until it is as creamy as you like.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wrap in foil unbrowned chicken with all ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Put in large bowl.
Cut butter on top of mixture.
Pour milk and vanilla into mixture. Don't stir.
Cook
minutes on High.
Pour into pan until it hardens. Cool, then cut and eat.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop or grind as fine as you can.
Let stand in warm water 30 minutes with salt.
Drain.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Heat and seal. Makes 8 pints.

title: mom's molasses cookies
directions: Measure first 5 ingredients into sifter.
Cream shortening; add sugar; cream until fluffy.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and blend well. Form into small balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with 24 graham crackers (place side by side); set aside.

title: fruit sangria
directions: Mix juices of your choice of flavoring (example:
if you like more cranberry, put more cranberry juice in mixture), then mix club soda and Sprite to desired flavoring.
Chill before serving. Garnish with orange and lime slices.
You can use mint and lemon, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam.
Layer chicken, mixture of soup, sour cream and 1/2 of the stuffing mix.
Layer remaining stuffing on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: In saucepan,
melt
chocolate
and
butter; cool.
In a small bowl,
beat
together
the
eggs
and
the 1 teaspoon vanilla; gradually
add
the 3/4 cup sugar.
Continue beating until
thick and
lemon-colored.
Sift together flour, baking powder and
salt; add to egg mixture, beating well.
Blend in cooled chocolate mixture
and
the nuts; set aside.
In mixer bowl, cream
together cream
cheese
and
the remaining sugar until fluffy.
Blend in the remaining egg and vanilla.
Spread half of the chocolate mixture in greased and lightly floured 8 x 8

Pour cheese mixture over chocolate mixture; top
with spoonfuls
of the remaining chocolate mixture.
With
