swirl through layers to marble. Bake in a
oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 16.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Beat yolks of eggs until light; add to this.
Add milk.
Roll the crackers fine.
Mix baking powder with cracker crumbs; add this to other mixture, together with salt and chopped nuts.
Add beaten whites of eggs. Bake in 2 layers at 375°.
When cool, spread whipped cream (sweetened) between layers and on top of cake.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add other ingredients; stir.
Congeal.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Quickly fry 1 tortillas at a time in hot oil (375°) to soften.
Spoon a heaping tablespoonful of chicken mixture onto each.
Spread down center and roll.
Place seam side down in an oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
When all tortillas are filled and rolled, spoon over either green chilies or enchilada sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and enchiladas are hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend graham crackers into crumbs.
Melt margarine.
Pour over crumbs.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Coat blueberries with 3/4 cup sugar and set aside.
Pour pineapple into dish and then blueberries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Melt margarine and drizzle over mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and chopped pecans on top. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sugar snap peas with mushrooms
directions: Cook the sugar snap peas in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Slice the mushrooms.
Heat the butter and oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add the mushrooms and cook until they are soft and liquid has evaporated, 10 to 12 minutes.
Add peas, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper; heat through, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil.
Slice cucumbers and chop vegetables; mix.
Pour liquid over vegetables. Store in refrigerator in jars.
Stir daily for 4 to 5 days. Will keep in refrigerator.

title: microwave everyday meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Press into a 9-inch round glass cake dish.
Cover with a paper towel. Microwave 14 to 17 minutes.
Give dish a 1/4 turn twice during cooking.
If desired, spread catsup over top of meat loaf and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lazy lasagne
directions: Brown the ground meat and salt in Dutch oven; drain the fat. Add spaghetti mix, tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil and a generous amount of Parmesan cheese; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter and Wesson oil.
Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Add a small amount of milk and flour mixture at a time.
Beat well.
Add lemon and vanilla extract.
Bake in large tube pan at 300°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bessie's pound cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar, Crisco and milk for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix 1 minute on medium speed.
Cook in large pan 45 minutes at 225°.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place all ingredients into big saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and cook two hours.
Add sausage to beans the last 30 minutes of cooking time.

title: pecan crescent danish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour, nuts, cinnamon and butter.
Mix well.
Separate crescent dough into two large rectangles.
Overlap long sides of rectangles.
Firmly press edges and perforations to seal (this prevents separation during baking).
Spread sugar and nut mixture over dough.
Starting at shorter side, roll up, pressing edges to seal.
Cut into 16 slices.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white.
Bake for 12 to 18 minutes until golden brown.
Frost while warm.

title: pannekeeken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine eggs, flour and milk in a mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly with a wire whisk.
Heat butter in 10-inch frying pan in oven while preheating.
Add batter and bake for 25 minutes or until pancake is puffed and golden.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve like normal pancake.
Serves 2.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Brown rice and onions in butter or margarine.
Separately, flour chicken and lightly brown in oil.
Place mushrooms, rice, onion, and broth in large buttered casserole dish.
Add chicken, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery, nuts and mayonnaise; toss.
If desired, mound salad in lettuce cups and garnish with maraschino cherries. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Can use crunchy peanut butter (use a little more if using crunchy peanut butter).

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, vanilla and oats, stirring between each item in order.
May add 1 cup nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine.
Add peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and freeze.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip frozen candy in mixture.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Make cake according to box directions.
Make stack or sheet cake.
Cool completely.
Mix all other ingredients in a medium saucepan; heat over medium heat until of smooth spreading consistency.
Spread on cool cake and enjoy.

title: crab meat dip
directions: In a 2-quart dish, saute butter, onion, parsley and celery on High for 4 minutes. Stir in cream cheese and microwave on High for 1 minute. Add garlic powder, Tabasco sauce, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well. Fold crab meat in gently and microwave on High for 4 minutes; serve with crackers or Melba toast.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone.
Cut in small pieces.
Mix in a large bowl the chicken, soups and sour cream. In a 13 x 9-inch pan, line bottom with crackers. Dot with butter.
Pour chicken mixture on top. Crumble crackers on top and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with slivered almonds.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and salt in top of a double boiler. Combine egg yolks and milk; stir into flour mixture and blend well.
Cook over hot water until thickened, stirring constantly. Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Cool slightly and stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Before serving, top with cream and sprinkle with the coconut.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix melted butter with box of muffin mix and both cans of corn and sour cream.
Add slightly beaten eggs. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg substitute and sweetener to creamed mixture; beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Stir flour, oat bran, baking powder and soda to blend well.
Add bananas to creamed mixture, along with flour mixture; beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Add nuts to batter; mix lightly.
Spread evenly in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Cut into 14 equal slices, then serve.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Combine flour, pecans and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° and cool.
(Will turn slightly white.) Cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 small carton of Cool Whip with ingredients.
Make butterscotch (add milk).
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Add butterscotch mixture next.
Then top with large carton of Cool Whip.
Finish with chopped pecans. Refrigerate.

title: barbari bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in very warm water; add oil.
Add 1 cup flour and salt.
Add flour in small amounts, stirring until stiff dough is formed.
Place in greased bowl, cover and place in warm place to rise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Knock down and knead until soft. Divide in 4 parts.
Grease 4 baking sheets.
Flatten each piece and shape into flat oblong loaves about 1/4-inch thick.
Make 3 lengthwise ridges on each loaf with the side of hand.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Cover with cloth and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serve at once.

title: george's cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, water and eggs together.
Grate chocolate and add to first mixture.
Add chocolate chips and stir. Pour into greased and sugared tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool for 3 to 4 minutes and turn onto rack or plate.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Gradually add egg yolks, beating well. Add soda to buttermilk.
Add alternately, buttermilk and flour, to sugar mixture while beating slowly.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour mixture into 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 cake in bottom of punch bowl, then layer 1/2 of pudding, 1 can pineapple, 1 can pie filling, 1 container Cool Whip, 1 cup pecans and repeat as listed, layered with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours (can be made the night before).

title: chicken elegant
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add the rest.
Heat and serve on toast points, rice or puff pastry shells.

title: margaret bobbit's barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce.
Chill for several hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: hamilton cooler
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator until ready to use.
Pour over ice and add a little ginger ale.

title: mock wild rice
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a heavy skillet over low heat. Add soup mix, rice, water and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg and add the flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Add buttermilk and vegetable oil.
Whisk until mixture is smooth.
Fold in fresh blueberries.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter onto hot lightly greased griddle.
Turn when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked.
Yield:
8 pancakes.

title: baked red snapper fillets
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Lightly dust with flour. Shake off excess.
Place in single layer in lightly greased shallow casserole.
Cover completely with sauce.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with forks.
Garnish with chives.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with a rolling pin.
Chop cherries and nuts, keeping out 4 whole cherries and 16 pecan halves.
Mix cherries, nuts and raisins with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and milk.
To this mixture, add fruit, nuts and Jackson's vanilla wafers mixture, mixing well.
Let stand while
preparing pan with wax paper.
Pack in pan.
Decorate top with cherries and pecan halves.
Bake in moderate oven, 325°, for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients until well mixed.
Place mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, celery and 1 cup almonds.
Mix all remaining ingredients and add to chicken mixture. Chill for several hours.
Serves 6 on lettuce leaves.
Sprinkle with remaining almonds.

title: chicken and biscuit casserole
directions: In a greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan, mix bacon, chicken, vegetables, tomatoes and 2/3 cup grated cheese.
Blend soup and milk; pour over ingredients in pan and stir.
Cover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.
Combine Bisquick, milk and 1/2 can onions.
Drop by spoonfuls to form biscuits on top.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Top with cheese; bake until melted.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Layer in casserole dish in roaster.
Cover and place in a 250° oven.
Forget it for 5 hours; do not stir until ready to serve. Do not disturb while baking.

title: chili
directions: In large saucepan, cook and crumble meat until almost brown. Add onions, pepper and garlic.
Cook until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes. Remember this is a pudding, not a pie. Goes good with a tea cake.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients well; roll in desired shape and bake until light brown at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: beef in cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Brown beef with onion, drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, set aside.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles on ungreased cookie sheet.
Overlap long sides; firmly press perforations and edges to seal.
Form a 15 x 13 inch rectangle. Spread meat mixture lengthwise in a 4 inch wide strip, down center of dough to with in one inch of ends.
Top with cheese.
Fold shorter sides of dough 1 inch over filling.
Bring long sides of dough over filling, over lapping edges; pinch edges to seal. Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake for 20- 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together cornstarch and
sugar.
Add
cup
milk. Beat together eggs and 2 cups milk.
Mix all together and keep stirring.
Cook slow until thickened;
then beat in vanilla, 3 cups milk and evaporated milk.
Makes
one gallon.
Serve with your favorite fruit toppings.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, vanilla, salt, water, flour and oleo.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Peel and core apples.
Stretch and wrap each apple half in 1 biscuit.
Lay wrapped apple, flat side down, in baking dish.
Pour hot sauce over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until a beautiful golden brown, basting occasionally while baking.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together and put into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour and salt and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add soda and vanilla.
Add red food coloring, mixing well.
Bake in three 8-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: key lime pie
directions: Put gelatin and lime rind into blender container.
Add boiling water.
Cover and blend at medium speed until gelatin is dissolved and rind is finely chopped.
Add lime juice and egg yolks.
Cover, blend at medium speed until thoroughly mixed.
Add condensed milk. Cover and blend at medium speed until mixed.
Beat egg whites with electric mixer until stiff, but not dry.
Fold gently into lime mixture.
Turn into crust.
Chill until set.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well.
Mix all other ingredients with drained fruit.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: raspberry icebox dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine gelatin and water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.	Fold in raspberries.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until syrupy.
In a small bowl, combine the cracker crumbs, brown sugar and butter.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
In a mixing bowl, beat the milk and pudding mix on low speed for 2 minutes.
In another bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add the pudding mixture.
Layer over crust.
Spoon gelatin mixture over the top.
Chill until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Blend oleo and sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Alternate flour mixture with 1/2 cup milk and oleo mixture.
Lay peaches in bottom of pan (1 large can of peaches, drained).
Pour mixture over top.
In separate bowl, mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and 3/4 cup sugar. Sprinkle over top.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: waffles
directions: Mix eggs with milk and salt.
Sift the flour and baking powder together.	Add
to
liquid.
When ingredients are well mixed, stir
in
lard.
Bake
in waffle iron until done.
(Use about
3/4 cup mix for each waffle.) Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Makes 5 waffles.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Combine asparagus, crackers and eggs.
Cut eggs in quarters. Make a rich white sauce using liquid from the asparagus, butter and milk.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add 1/2 cup shredded cheese and a pinch of garlic is optional.
Pour white sauce over other ingredients and stir.
Roll about 6 crackers and sprinkle over top dotted with butter.
Bake at about 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: In a roaster (no lid) mix everything together.
Bake at 325°, stirring 2 to 3 times per hour, until thick.
Pour into hot jars and process 10 minutes or freeze after the jars cool.
Yields nearly 7 pints.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Add 1 cup of chicken broth.
Add chicken breasts that have been broken into small pieces.
Add soups that have been mixed with water as can directs. To the stuffing mix, add melted margarine and 1 cup of broth; spread over casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes.

title: ham creole
directions: Cook chopped onion and chopped pepper in 2 tablespoons fat for a few minutes. Add stewed tomatoes. Simmer for 10 minutes. Add ham cubes and cook 5 minutes longer. Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck or turkey and drain fat.
In a large pot, add onion soup mix to meat.
Stir in chili beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, salsa and chili seasoning.
Cook until hot.
Feeds about 6.

title: zesty carrots(serves 8)
directions: Mix onion, horseradish and mayonnaise together with the liquid.
Place cooked carrots in a buttered casserole dish.
Pour mixture over top of carrots.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: In a large skillet, cut bacon into small pieces and cook to crisp stage; drain.
Add hamburger, stirring until done.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, rice, tomato sauce plus 1/2 can water.
With lid on, simmer for approximately 20 minutes, or until rice is done.
If too dry, add either more water or tomato sauce (to taste).
Just before serving and while still hot, grate cheese over top.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, brown sugar and rolled oats.
Cut in butter until blended.
Press 2/3 in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread this crust with the jam. Sprinkle on the remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes. Cool and cut.
Makes 24 bars.

title: beefy chili soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Mix and knead into ball (in mixing bowl) the first 5 ingredients.
Set aside in warm place and cover with a towel for 1 hour.
Toss or roll into a circle on greased pizza pan.
Add pizza sauce and cheese.
You may add any other ingredients that you may wish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let sit for 2 to 3 minutes before cutting.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and pat into cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour on crust.
Return to oven for 25 minutes longer. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine the flour and salt; set aside.
Cream the oleo and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Add 1/2 cup flour mixture to the coconut.
Add buttermilk mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Add candy mixture.
Turn into 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth. Add the next 6 ingredients; mix well. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal. Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle. Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture; twist slightly and seal edges. Brush tops with reserved 1 tablespoon margarine. Dip in crouton crumbs. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: polish chop suey
directions: Brown and drain beef and onion.
Add to cooked cabbage and cooked noodles.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, eggs and oil. Stir until blended.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Grease well and flour a Bundt cake pan.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of nut mixture in bottom.
Spoon in 1/2 of cake batter on top.
Top this with remaining mixture; then put in rest of the batter.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put drained vegetables in a casserole dish.
Spread raw hamburger over vegetables.
Pour soup over meat.
Lay Tater Tots over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
A nice meal in one dish.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Drain the green beans; wrap a half piece of bacon around 5 or 6 green beans. Place them, seam side down, in a glass 9 x 12 baking dish. When the dish is full, pour the whole bottle of dressing over the bean bundles. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hobo supper
directions: Will need a 12-inch square of foil for each serving.

title: mom's favorite recipe
directions: Place all in well-greased car and head for nearest restaurant.

title: patti's fried chicken
directions: Wash the chicken and pat dry. Marinate chicken in covered bowl of the buttermilk. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually add sugar until thick.
Add remaining ingredients, then process in ice cream machine.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt the margarine and cocoa in a saucepan on low.
Take off heat, then add the sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix with wooden spoon and cool for awhile.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls into powdered sugar. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, until just set.

title: dewberry pie
directions: Place dewberries into pie shells.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over berries.
Mix last 3 ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle over custard and berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: cherry chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine chicken, pasta, celery, onions, and cherries.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in baking pan by directions on box.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in top of cake, pour whole can of Eagle Brand milk over cake.
It will soak into cake.
Make icing by recipe box.
Ice cake and sprinkle coconut over top.
Delicious.

title: pumpkin cake(very easy to prepare and freezes well.)
directions: Combine all cake ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer, until thoroughly blended.
Add raisins.
Pour batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
For variety, try white pecans or chopped pecan or walnuts to the cake batter.

title: "bola's" chocolate pie
directions: Mix
flour
into sugar.
Add cocoa, milk and egg yolks. Cook in	double	boiler until thick.
Add vanilla and butter; cool. Whip
whites of eggs and after filling has cooled, pour into crust.
Top with meringue.	Brown top in oven.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Mix cheese and pineapple in bowl.
Pour flour and sugar over pineapple and mix.
Put into 9x13 glass baking dish.	Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of pineapple mixture.
Melt butter and pour over Ritz crackers.
Pour juice over crackers.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 15-20.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Beat constantly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat hard after each egg.
Fold in flour and pour into a buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato-tuna salad
directions: Place potatoes in saucepan; cover with water and boil until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain potatoes and cut into bite-size pieces.
Toss potatoes with remaining ingredients and refrigerate until cold.
Yield:
about 6 cups.
Per serving:
Calories:
135. Carbohydrate:
15 g. Protein:
10 g. Fat:
4 g. Sodium:
352 mg. Exchanges per serving:
1 starch/bread and 1 lean meat.

title: picnic passion
directions: In a medium size mixing bowl, combine pineapple and pudding mix.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cherries.
Fold together.
Garnish, if desired.
Chill until serving time.

title: brown's cream cheese and onion spread
directions: Get cream cheese soft.
Add chopped onion, olives and cheese; then add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Better if left overnight before using.
Good on crackers or whole wheat bread.

title: charlotte's chicken & rice
directions: Boil one whole chicken.
When done, debone and strain the broth.
Add two cups of rice to the broth and cook rice per directions.
Add deboned chicken, two cans of cream of mushroom soup, and one can of cream of chicken soup, onion, celery seed and black pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk gravy
directions: Melt grease in a skillet.
Add meal and brown.
Add salt and pepper; brown some more.
Add buttermilk and water; stir until thick.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar and water in heavy saucepan.
Cook to 246° on candy thermometer, firm-ball stage. Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Fold in remaining.
Beat well; put in 3 (1 pound) coffee cans or 2 bread pans (greased). Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put a pan of water in the oven for moisture.

title: lemon whipper snaps
directions: Combine cake mix, topping and egg.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into sugar.
Roll in balls.
Place on a Pam sprayed cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Place on wire rack to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Prick bottom of unbaked pie shell with fork and rub a mixture of 1 tablespoon each flour and sugar into holes (this prevents a soggy crust).
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Reduce heat to 300°.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place seasoning packet and butter in bowl. Add water, then stuffing mix.
Toss.
Mix soup and milk in casserole dish.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Cover with stuffing.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients as listed, stirring well as moistened.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch skillet.
Bake at 425° for 25 or 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: clam spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 9-inch layer cake pan or quiche dish.
Spread mixture evenly in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with your favorite crackers.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in buttered pie plate. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: patchworks pasta
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Chop heads and stems of broccoli. Crumble the bacon.
Mix everything together.
Add Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar as the dressing.
Cool before serving.

title: fettucini with spinach
directions: In a large skillet, cook spinach and garlic in oil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Dissolve bouillon in water or spinach juice.
Add bouillon mixture, basil and cottage cheese to spinach.
Stir over low heat to blend.
Toss spinach mixture, grated cheeses and noodles together in a large bowl that has been heated.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Refrigerate leftovers, if there are any.
Serve with garlic bread or breadsticks.

title: polish stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage, removing each leaf just as it becomes tender. Drain leaves.
Mix ground beef, rice and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Line bottom of 4 1/2-quart pot with sauerkraut.
Place 3 to 4 tablespoons of meat mixture in center of leaf and roll, bringing in sides of leaf as you roll.
Arrange cabbage rolls in pot, stacking as you go.
Place remaining leaves over top.
Pour V-8 juice over top.
Simmer on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: sandbakkles
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Put in sandbakkle tins.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter and m&m cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In a mixer bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture; beat until well combined.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar, if desired.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet; crisscross with tines of a fork. Bake in a 375° oven about 10 minutes.
Press M&M's into cookies before baking.
Makes 48.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together and place aside.
Cream shortening with sugar and add beaten eggs and beat until mixture is smooth and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and really beat.
Fold flour mixture into sugar mixture and add vanilla.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add lemon juice and put in refrigerator until it gets slightly thickened.
Blend or whip cream cheese and sugar, then whip or blend large can of Pet milk to cream cheese and sugar.
(Optional to add extra half of lemon juice to Pet milk and cream cheese and sugar mixture while blending.)
Mix jello mixture with cream cheese, sugar and milk until creamy.
Pour into crust and chill for several hours.

title: sheet cake(for birthday, etc.)
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix flours together.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Cook in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Grease bottom only.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: gallon jug muffins
directions: Mix together oats, All-Bran, shredded wheat (4 large biscuits) and oil.
Pour boiling water over all and let cool.
Then add buttermilk, eggs and sugar and mix.
Sift together salt, flour and baking soda.
Mix all together well and store in glass gallon jar in refrigerator.
Keeps fresh up to 3 months.

title: crab balls
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil.
Mix rest of the ingredients together and shape into balls.
Deep fry until brown. Serve hot or cold with seafood sauce.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Sift together 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then gradually add remaining flour until dough is stiff enough to handle.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board and shape with floured cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with plain or tinted sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fried fish batter
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Coat fish with pancake mix.
Dip fillets in batter.
Fry 4 to 6 minutes.

title: rice, cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole (2-quart).
Bake uncovered for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
May top with cracker crumbs if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients together.
Add the flour mixture to the wet mixture and mix well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Place on a greased cookie sheet by teaspoon and bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: 1) Brown beef with onion.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix in large pan and cook over low heat.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Cook to desired consistency, about 2 hours. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 35 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and add all remaining ingredients except bacon. Mix well and put in greased loaf pan.
Top with bacon slices. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with green peas.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and roll into 1-inch balls.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and wax.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper and cool.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken. While boiling, scrape away top layer of film. Add vegetables.
Cook until tender. Strain.
Cook spaghetti in broth.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients in a 4-quart heavy gauge aluminum pot. While this is boiling, burn 4 tablespoons sugar on the side in a Teflon pot until dark brown.
Remove from heat.
When cooled enough, add about a cupful of the candy mixture.
Stir until well mixed to keep from caramelizing, then pour back into mixture.
When soft ball forms when added to cold water, remove from heat and add a pinch of soda and vanilla.
Beat until it's ready to drop on slightly greased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Put eggs in medium bowl and beat with a fork until fluffy.
Mix other ingredients into eggs, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Pour into 9-inch prepared or frozen crust.
Bake at 350° on bottom rack.
Pie is done when center shakes like congealed jello and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes one pie.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: chicken in cream and butter sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Flour chicken and place in greased baking dish, uncovered.
Bake until golden brown (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Remove from oven and put butter on top of chicken. Bake until butter is melted.
Remove from oven and cover the chicken 2/3 of the way with milk.
Cover and place back in oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: passover brownies
directions: Melt margarine and 3 ounces of chocolate in pan in a 325° oven.
In bowl, beat 2 eggs, sugar and cake meal. Add melted shortening and chocolate mixture.
Beat well and add remaining chocolate bits.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch pecan fudge
directions: Combine pudding mix, brown sugar, milk, sugar, pecans, butter and vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat until cool.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrot in bowl.
Add diced celery.
Mix all other ingredients in small bowl and thin with milk or cream to your taste.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Mix together.
Chill and serve.

title: christmas gumbo
directions: Cook together for 10 minutes the butter, onion, celery, carrots and turnips. Add peppercorns, bay leaves, cloves, vinegar, water, lemon peel and fish.

title: country ham-redeye gravy
directions: Place ham slices in a cold cast-iron skillet.
Cook over medium heat until fat is crisp, turning several times for even cooking.
Remove ham to warm platter.
Pour excess fat from skillet, leaving about 2 tablespoons.
Stir sugar into fat and meat drippings in skillet.
Add coffee and water; heat to boiling. Serve over ham slices.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Mix other ingredients with yeast.
Let
stand	15
minutes
after
cutting
out and before putting
in
oven.	Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°. (Can be frozen.)

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat and add milk; add cocoa and sugar.
Stir well, then turn setting to high and bring to a boil. Boil one minute on high, then turn down one notch and boil 1 1/2 to 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla (and nuts, if desired).
Place pan in cold water and beat fudge until it loses its gloss and thickens enough to spoon onto waxed paper.

title: impossible quiche
directions: In blender, combine and blend for 1 minute the eggs, milk, Bisquick, cheese and butter.
Grease and flour a 9 to 10-inch pie pan.
Place in bottom of dish the bacon, ham or sausage, onions and green pepper.
Pour blender mixture over chopped items.
Let stand for 5 minutes before baking.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and pepper over top and bake 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish, mix soup, water, and rice. Pour in a casserole dish and arrange chicken pieces on top. Sprinkle dried soup on top and cover with aluminum foil and cook in oven for 1 hour at 370°.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and mayonnaise, add fruit cocktail, oranges and marshmallows; mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Cool Whip and place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: authentic irish cabbage rolls
directions: Remove core from cabbage (as much as possible).
Boil whole cabbage until it is soft enough to roll the leaves, but not fully cooked.
Leaves will peel off, one at a time.

title: one leg turkey and dressing
directions: Cut off one leg and thigh of turkey.
Cook, using broth for dressing, plus broth from baking turkey.
Mix bread ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Next, cool bread.
Mix with broth, eggs, celery, onion, deboned turkey meat and salt and pepper to taste.
When you think too soupy, mixture is just right to bake.
(No dry dressing.)
Bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes or until light brown and bubbly.

title: banana nut bread(makes 3 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs, bananas and oleo. Add to dry ingredients and stir just enough to combine. Add nuts. Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Put crushed pineapple, sugar and lemon juice in pan; simmer for 5 minutes.
Dissolve lemon jello in 2 1/3 cups hot water. Stir in previous ingredients with jello; mix well and set in refrigerator until almost firm.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and the whipping cream.
Set until firm.

title: better than ever cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions, using milk instead of water. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat pineapple with sugar.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour hot pineapple mixture over cake.
Mix pudding according to directions; blend in cream cheese.
Spread on cooled cake.
Slice bananas over pudding mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip, coconut and cherries.

title: clothes pin cookies
directions: Add sugar to flour.
Cut in 1/4 of the Fluffo.
Add eggs and water.
Mix as for dough.
Place dough in refrigerator for 1 hour, then roll out and spread with 1/4 of Fluffo (fold like envelope). Repeat this 3 times.
Will take 3 hours in all.
Take 1/4 of the dough at a time and roll.
Cut into 8-inch strips.
Wind loosely around clothespins.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes, then at 375° for 10 minutes.
Work off pins and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl, combine sugar, oil and egg. In another bowl, combine baking soda, salt and vanilla; add to sugar combination.
Alternately add flour; mix well.
Fold in raw rhubarb and nuts; spoon into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4 x 3-inch bread pans.
Combine sugar and melted butter; mix thoroughly. Scatter on top of dough.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately; cool.

title: easy chili
directions: In a
4 quart pan, brown beef, sausage and onion.
When brown, add
soup,	puree,	tomatoes
and seasoning.
Add 1 (14 ounce) can water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Stir often.
If mixture becomes too thick, add water to desired thickness and simmer.
Can be frozen.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Stir well.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of the mixture into mold (set other aside).
Put mold into refrigerator.
When mixture is firm, spread most of the sour cream on top, then add liquid mixture that has been set aside.
Set mold in refrigerator until set.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add marshmallow cream.
When well blended, add Cool Whip.
Serve with chunks of cantaloupe, honeydew, melon, pineapple, apple, banana, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: chicago style deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Brown ground meat and onion; drain off grease.
Stir in pizza sauce, Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer while preparing crust. Arrange biscuits in pan.
Press over bottom and sides.
Parbake for 10 minutes.
Spoon on meat mixture. Put on mushrooms, etc. Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Place flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Mix well.
Add Crisco and mix until crumbly.
In small bowl mix 1/2 cup water, vinegar and egg. Combine two mixtures and stir well with fork. Makes 3 to 4 (9-inch) crusts.

title: apple pudding dessert
directions: Combine the flour, oleo and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Pat this crust mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cherry dessert squares
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and melted oleo by hand.
Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over cake mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Drizzle with glaze mixture when cooled.
Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: the big dipper
directions: Cook chili in a medium saucepan until hot. Spread cream cheese and cover a 10-inch round dish. Pour heated chili over cream cheese. Spread shredded cheese over chili layer and top evenly. Dip Fritos Scoops into dip and enjoy!

title: party smokies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Slice bacon strips in thirds. Wrap 1/3 bacon strip around a Little Smokie. Secure bacon with a toothpick. Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar to cover. Drizzle water on top. Bake until bacon is cooked (around 50 minutes).

title: vegetables, different ways
directions: Season with your choice Hi-Energy Onion, Chicken, Asparagus, Mushroom Soup Supplements, etc., and canola oil.

title: pot o' beans
directions: Fry, drain and crumble bacon.
Leave grease in pan and add next 6 ingredients.
Drain beans.
Add beans and bacon to mixture. Cook slowly 20 minutes on stove, then bake, covered, 30 to 45 minutes at 375° or use crock-pot.

title: swedish apple pie(easy, quick, yummy dessert)
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together with a fork.
Grease pie plate.
Peel and core apples (enough to fill to heaping); put into pie plate and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon dough on top of fruit and bake at 325° until golden brown or about 1 hour.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and condensed milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip until all mixed together; pour into crust.
Refrigerate until set.

title: easy guacamole dip
directions: In a small bowl with a fork mash soft ripe avocados.
Add dash of lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add garlic powder if desired.
Blend in one jar of Gerber garden vegetable.
Add picante sauce and garnish with nacho chips and enjoy.

title: microwave apple crunch
directions: To the oleo, stir in the next 5 ingredients.
Mix and set aside.
In an 8-inch square microwave-safe dish, put the sliced apples.
Toss with the sugar.
Sprinkle topping evenly over apples.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes on High.
Rotate halfway through.
Let stand on heatproof surface for 30 minutes.

title: lemon herb seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Toss gently with a spoon until well blended.
Store in an airtight container in a cool, dry, dark place for up to six months.
Makes approximately 1 cup.
Use with chicken, fish and turkey.

title: play dough for children
directions: Mix together, then heat in a frypan until cooked through, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Turn onto table and knead.
Add a few drops of food coloring.

title: shrimp dish
directions: Boil shrimp 7 minutes or until pink.
Chill.
Remove shells and devein.
Chop into small pieces.

title: cucumber-onion salad
directions: If you like, sugar to your own taste (I like about 6 teaspoons).
Peel and thinly slice cucumbers and onion.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Marinate for several hours in the refrigerator.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Bring the tomatoes and sugar to a rolling boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Turn off heat.
Add the Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix well.
Shape; roll in flour and fry.
Place in skillet. Cover with mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Simmer until done.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, peanut butter, sugars and eggs. Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix together.
Roll in walnut size balls and flatten with a fork or bottom of a glass.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: noodles and tomatoes
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Drain water and add tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add squash and flour.
Mix well.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Boil 6 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in pectin; boil 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Quickly pour hot jelly into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes. Yields 7 half-pints.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This is a heavy sweet cake for strawberries, etc. (somewhat like a sugar cookie).

title: rice and black bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Before serving, use this topping:

title: potatoes poupon
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, cook shallots in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in cream, mustard and remaining butter or margarine.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to low; add 1/2 cup shredded cheese and basil, stirring until cheese melts.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Add broth to chicken.
Mix croutons, onion and celery together.
Add soup and chicken with broth.
Put into a large oiled casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, including sugar into a large mixing.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Divide batter into greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream the margarine and confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and salt.
Mix and add pecans.
Roll in balls.
Put on cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar after cool.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: Place uncooked ground beef in bottom of 9-inch square baking dish.
Cover with a layer of onion slices.
Add a layer of frozen Tater Tots, covering beef and onion.
Spread soup evenly over top. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken surprise casserole
directions: Place chicken, potatoes, milk, soup and corn in greased casserole.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: Place chicken in oblong pan.
Top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese.
Top with tomatoes.
Combine margarine and stuffing; sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with oregano (optional).

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese; stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans and seasoned salt.
Mix everything and let harden.
Form into ball and roll in remaining pecans.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo, and 1 C. nuts together.
Put into the bottom of a 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool. Cream the cheese and sugar.
Fold in 1 C. Cool Whip; spread on first layer.
Mix well the vanilla pudding and milk.
Pour onto the second layer and spread out.
Use remaining whipped topping and pour over third layer.
Cover with nut halves, shaved chocolate or coconut.
Refrigerate.
Can be made a day ahead and kept in the refrigerator.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Cook macaroni in a large amount of boiling water until tender. Drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Melt fat in a large skillet.
Add onion and cook until lightly browned.
Add beef, salt and pepper; cook until meat is done.
Add macaroni, tomatoes and chili powder. Turn mixture into baking dish and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: heavenly harmony rhubarb
directions: In small bowl mix flour, sugar and oleo.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
In medium bowl, mix egg yolks, 2 cups white sugar, flour, salt, cream and rhubarb.
Pour over crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Top with meringue made with egg whites, 8 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Beat whites; add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add vanilla.
Spread on cake and brown lightly.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion when beef is done.
Remove from heat and cover.
Mix chopped lettuce, diced tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Add bag of crumbled Doritos.
Mix with Catalina dressing until well coated.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soups, tomatoes, broth, milk, olives and chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Grease or Pam a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Layer chicken mixture and tortillas, ending with chicken mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oleo and dates.
Cook for 5 minutes. Pour in Krispies and pecans.
Butter hands; make into balls and roll in coconut flakes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Press butter, peanut butter, cracker crumbs and sugar into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not bake.
Spread topping over peanut butter mixture and refrigerate; then cut into squares.

title: fun sub
directions: Thaw bread dough as instructed on package.
Roll into rectangle, then cut strips on each side, approximately 2-inches deep.
Fill center with meats, cheese and dressing.
Braid the strips of bread over center of meats.
Brush top with egg white. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: microwave fried chicken
directions: Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken. Arrange pieces, skin side up, in microwavable dish, with thickest part toward edges.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave additional 8 to 12 minutes until done.

title: mix casserole
directions: Brown in butter, onion, hamburger meat and bell pepper.
Place in large bowl and mix all the other ingredients to it.
